34CGBlockInfo::CGBlockInfo(const BlockDecl *block, StringRef name)
35 : Name(name), CXXThisIndex(0), CanBeGlobal(false), NeedsCopyDispose(false),
36 HasCXXObject(false), UsesStret(false), HasCapturedVariableLayout(false),
37 CapturesNonExternalType(false), LocalAddress(Address::invalid()),
38 StructureType(nullptr), Block(block), DominatingIP(nullptr) {
39
40 // Skip asm prefix, if any. 'name' is usually taken directly from
41 // the mangled name of the enclosing function.
42 if (!name.empty() && name[0] == '\01')
43 name = name.substr(1);
44}

66static llvm::Value *getFunctionPointer(CodeGenFunction &CGF, llvm::Value *V) {
67 if (CGF.getContext().getTargetInfo().areAllPointersCapabilities())
68 return CodeGenFunction::FunctionAddressToCapability(CGF, V);
69 return V;
70}

74/// Represents a type of copy/destroy operation that should be performed for an
75/// entity that's captured by a block.
76enum class BlockCaptureEntityKind {
77 CXXRecord, // Copy or destroy
78 ARCWeak,
79 ARCStrong,
80 NonTrivialCStruct,
81 BlockObject, // Assign or release
82 None
83};
84
85/// Represents a captured entity that requires extra operations in order for
86/// this entity to be copied or destroyed correctly.
87struct BlockCaptureManagedEntity {
88 BlockCaptureEntityKind CopyKind, DisposeKind;
89 BlockFieldFlags CopyFlags, DisposeFlags;
90 const BlockDecl::Capture *CI;
91 const CGBlockInfo::Capture *Capture;
92
93 BlockCaptureManagedEntity(BlockCaptureEntityKind CopyType,
94 BlockCaptureEntityKind DisposeType,
95 BlockFieldFlags CopyFlags,
96 BlockFieldFlags DisposeFlags,
97 const BlockDecl::Capture &CI,
98 const CGBlockInfo::Capture &Capture)
99 : CopyKind(CopyType), DisposeKind(DisposeType), CopyFlags(CopyFlags),
100 DisposeFlags(DisposeFlags), CI(&CI), Capture(&Capture) {}
101
102 bool operator<(const BlockCaptureManagedEntity &Other) const {
103 return Capture->getOffset() < Other.Capture->getOffset();
104 }
105};
106
107enum class CaptureStrKind {
108 // String for the copy helper.
109 CopyHelper,
110 // String for the dispose helper.
111 DisposeHelper,
112 // Merge the strings for the copy helper and dispose helper.
113 Merged
114};
115
116} // end anonymous namespace

123 CaptureStrKind StrKind,
124 CharUnits BlockAlignment,
125 CodeGenModule &CGM);

127static std::string getBlockDescriptorName(const CGBlockInfo &BlockInfo,
128 CodeGenModule &CGM) {
129 std::string Name = "__block_descriptor_";
130 Name += llvm::to_string(BlockInfo.BlockSize.getQuantity()) + "_";
131
132 if (BlockInfo.needsCopyDisposeHelpers()) {
133 if (CGM.getLangOpts().Exceptions)
134 Name += "e";
135 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().ObjCAutoRefCountExceptions)
136 Name += "a";
137 Name += llvm::to_string(BlockInfo.BlockAlign.getQuantity()) + "_";
138
139 SmallVector<BlockCaptureManagedEntity, 4> ManagedCaptures;
140 findBlockCapturedManagedEntities(BlockInfo, CGM.getContext().getLangOpts(),
141 ManagedCaptures);
142
143 for (const BlockCaptureManagedEntity &E : ManagedCaptures) {
144 Name += llvm::to_string(E.Capture->getOffset().getQuantity());
145
146 if (E.CopyKind == E.DisposeKind) {
147 // If CopyKind and DisposeKind are the same, merge the capture
148 // information.
149 assert(E.CopyKind != BlockCaptureEntityKind::None &&
150 "shouldn't see BlockCaptureManagedEntity that is None");
151 Name += getBlockCaptureStr(E, CaptureStrKind::Merged,
152 BlockInfo.BlockAlign, CGM);
153 } else {
154 // If CopyKind and DisposeKind are not the same, which can happen when
155 // either Kind is None or the captured object is a __strong block,
156 // concatenate the copy and dispose strings.
157 Name += getBlockCaptureStr(E, CaptureStrKind::CopyHelper,
158 BlockInfo.BlockAlign, CGM);
159 Name += getBlockCaptureStr(E, CaptureStrKind::DisposeHelper,
160 BlockInfo.BlockAlign, CGM);
161 }
162 }
163 Name += "_";
164 }
165
166 std::string TypeAtEncoding =
167 CGM.getContext().getObjCEncodingForBlock(BlockInfo.getBlockExpr());
168 /// Replace occurrences of '@' with '\1'. '@' is reserved on ELF platforms as
169 /// a separator between symbol name and symbol version.
170 std::replace(TypeAtEncoding.begin(), TypeAtEncoding.end(), '@', '\1');
171 Name += "e" + llvm::to_string(TypeAtEncoding.size()) + "_" + TypeAtEncoding;
172 Name += "l" + CGM.getObjCRuntime().getRCBlockLayoutStr(CGM, BlockInfo);
173 return Name;
174}

176/// buildBlockDescriptor - Build the block descriptor meta-data for a block.
177/// buildBlockDescriptor is accessed from 5th field of the Block_literal
178/// meta-data and contains stationary information about the block literal.
179/// Its definition will have 4 (or optionally 6) words.
180/// \code
181/// struct Block_descriptor {
182/// unsigned long reserved;
183/// unsigned long size; // size of Block_literal metadata in bytes.
184/// void *copy_func_helper_decl; // optional copy helper.
185/// void *destroy_func_decl; // optional destructor helper.
186/// void *block_method_encoding_address; // @encode for block literal signature.
187/// void *block_layout_info; // encoding of captured block variables.
188/// };
189/// \endcode
190static llvm::Constant *buildBlockDescriptor(CodeGenModule &CGM,
191 const CGBlockInfo &blockInfo) {
192 ASTContext &C = CGM.getContext();
193
194 llvm::IntegerType *ulong =
195 cast<llvm::IntegerType>(CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(C.UnsignedLongTy));
196 llvm::PointerType *i8p = nullptr;
197 if (CGM.getLangOpts().OpenCL)
198 i8p =
199 llvm::Type::getInt8PtrTy(
200 CGM.getLLVMContext(), CGM.getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_constant));
201 else
202 i8p = CGM.VoidPtrTy;
203
204 std::string descName;
205
206 // If an equivalent block descriptor global variable exists, return it.
207 if (C.getLangOpts().ObjC &&
208 CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::NonGC) {
209 descName = getBlockDescriptorName(blockInfo, CGM);
210 if (llvm::GlobalValue *desc = CGM.getModule().getNamedValue(descName))
211 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(desc,
212 CGM.getBlockDescriptorType());
213 }
214
215 // If there isn't an equivalent block descriptor global variable, create a new
216 // one.
217 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
218 auto elements = builder.beginStruct();
219
220 // reserved
221 elements.addInt(ulong, 0);
222
223 // Size
224 // FIXME: What is the right way to say this doesn't fit? We should give
225 // a user diagnostic in that case. Better fix would be to change the
226 // API to size_t.
227 elements.addInt(ulong, blockInfo.BlockSize.getQuantity());
228
229 // Optional copy/dispose helpers.
230 bool hasInternalHelper = false;
231 if (blockInfo.needsCopyDisposeHelpers()) {
232 // copy_func_helper_decl
233 llvm::Constant *copyHelper = buildCopyHelper(CGM, blockInfo);
234 elements.add(copyHelper);
235
236 // destroy_func_decl
237 llvm::Constant *disposeHelper = buildDisposeHelper(CGM, blockInfo);
238 elements.add(disposeHelper);
239
240 if (cast<llvm::Function>(copyHelper->getOperand(0))->hasInternalLinkage() ||
241 cast<llvm::Function>(disposeHelper->getOperand(0))
242 ->hasInternalLinkage())
243 hasInternalHelper = true;
244 }
245
246 // Signature. Mandatory ObjC-style method descriptor @encode sequence.
247 std::string typeAtEncoding =
248 CGM.getContext().getObjCEncodingForBlock(blockInfo.getBlockExpr());
249 elements.add(llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
250 CGM.GetAddrOfConstantCString(typeAtEncoding).getPointer(), i8p));
251
252 // GC layout.
253 if (C.getLangOpts().ObjC) {
254 if (CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() != LangOptions::NonGC)
255 elements.add(CGM.getObjCRuntime().BuildGCBlockLayout(CGM, blockInfo));
256 else
257 elements.add(CGM.getObjCRuntime().BuildRCBlockLayout(CGM, blockInfo));
258 }
259 else
260 elements.addNullPointer(i8p);
261
262 unsigned AddrSpace = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
263 if (C.getLangOpts().OpenCL)
264 AddrSpace = CGM.getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_constant);
265
266 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes linkage;
267 if (descName.empty()) {
268 linkage = llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage;
269 descName = "__block_descriptor_tmp";
270 } else if (hasInternalHelper) {
271 // If either the copy helper or the dispose helper has internal linkage,
272 // the block descriptor must have internal linkage too.
273 linkage = llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage;
274 } else {
275 linkage = llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage;
276 }
277
278 llvm::GlobalVariable *global =
279 elements.finishAndCreateGlobal(descName, CGM.getPointerAlign(),
280 /*constant*/ true, linkage, AddrSpace);
281
282 if (linkage == llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage) {
283 if (CGM.supportsCOMDAT())
284 global->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(descName));
285 global->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
286 global->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
287 }
288
289 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(global, CGM.getBlockDescriptorType());
290}

292/*
293 Purely notional variadic template describing the layout of a block.
294
295 template <class _ResultType, class... _ParamTypes, class... _CaptureTypes>
296 struct Block_literal {
297 /// Initialized to one of:
298 /// extern void *_NSConcreteStackBlock[];
299 /// extern void *_NSConcreteGlobalBlock[];
300 ///
301 /// In theory, we could start one off malloc'ed by setting
302 /// BLOCK_NEEDS_FREE, giving it a refcount of 1, and using
303 /// this isa:
304 /// extern void *_NSConcreteMallocBlock[];
305 struct objc_class *isa;
306
307 /// These are the flags (with corresponding bit number) that the
308 /// compiler is actually supposed to know about.
309 /// 23. BLOCK_IS_NOESCAPE - indicates that the block is non-escaping
310 /// 25. BLOCK_HAS_COPY_DISPOSE - indicates that the block
311 /// descriptor provides copy and dispose helper functions
312 /// 26. BLOCK_HAS_CXX_OBJ - indicates that there's a captured
313 /// object with a nontrivial destructor or copy constructor
314 /// 28. BLOCK_IS_GLOBAL - indicates that the block is allocated
315 /// as global memory
316 /// 29. BLOCK_USE_STRET - indicates that the block function
317 /// uses stret, which objc_msgSend needs to know about
318 /// 30. BLOCK_HAS_SIGNATURE - indicates that the block has an
319 /// @encoded signature string
320 /// And we're not supposed to manipulate these:
321 /// 24. BLOCK_NEEDS_FREE - indicates that the block has been moved
322 /// to malloc'ed memory
323 /// 27. BLOCK_IS_GC - indicates that the block has been moved to
324 /// to GC-allocated memory
325 /// Additionally, the bottom 16 bits are a reference count which
326 /// should be zero on the stack.
327 int flags;
328
329 /// Reserved; should be zero-initialized.
330 int reserved;
331
332 /// Function pointer generated from block literal.
333 _ResultType (*invoke)(Block_literal *, _ParamTypes...);
334
335 /// Block description metadata generated from block literal.
336 struct Block_descriptor *block_descriptor;
337
338 /// Captured values follow.
339 _CapturesTypes captures...;
340 };
341 */
342
343namespace {
344 /// A chunk of data that we actually have to capture in the block.
345 struct BlockLayoutChunk {
346 CharUnits Alignment;
347 CharUnits Size;
348 Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime Lifetime;
349 const BlockDecl::Capture *Capture; // null for 'this'
350 llvm::Type *Type;
351 QualType FieldType;
352
353 BlockLayoutChunk(CharUnits align, CharUnits size,
354 Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime lifetime,
355 const BlockDecl::Capture *capture,
356 llvm::Type *type, QualType fieldType)
357 : Alignment(align), Size(size), Lifetime(lifetime),
358 Capture(capture), Type(type), FieldType(fieldType) {}
359
360 /// Tell the block info that this chunk has the given field index.
361 void setIndex(CGBlockInfo &info, unsigned index, CharUnits offset) {
362 if (!Capture) {
363 info.CXXThisIndex = index;
364 info.CXXThisOffset = offset;
365 } else {
366 auto C = CGBlockInfo::Capture::makeIndex(index, offset, FieldType);
367 info.Captures.insert({Capture->getVariable(), C});
368 }
369 }
370 };
371
372 /// Order by 1) all __strong together 2) next, all byfref together 3) next,
373 /// all __weak together. Preserve descending alignment in all situations.
374 bool operator<(const BlockLayoutChunk &left, const BlockLayoutChunk &right) {
375 if (left.Alignment != right.Alignment)
376 return left.Alignment > right.Alignment;
377
378 auto getPrefOrder = [](const BlockLayoutChunk &chunk) {
379 if (chunk.Capture && chunk.Capture->isByRef())
380 return 1;
381 if (chunk.Lifetime == Qualifiers::OCL_Strong)
382 return 0;
383 if (chunk.Lifetime == Qualifiers::OCL_Weak)
384 return 2;
385 return 3;
386 };
387
388 return getPrefOrder(left) < getPrefOrder(right);
389 }
390} // end anonymous namespace
391
392/// Determines if the given type is safe for constant capture in C++.
393static bool isSafeForCXXConstantCapture(QualType type) {
394 const RecordType *recordType =
395 type->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe()->getAs<RecordType>();
396
397 // Only records can be unsafe.
398 if (!recordType) return true;
399
400 const auto *record = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(recordType->getDecl());
401
402 // Maintain semantics for classes with non-trivial dtors or copy ctors.
403 if (!record->hasTrivialDestructor()) return false;
404 if (record->hasNonTrivialCopyConstructor()) return false;
405
406 // Otherwise, we just have to make sure there aren't any mutable
407 // fields that might have changed since initialization.
408 return !record->hasMutableFields();
409}
410
411/// It is illegal to modify a const object after initialization.
412/// Therefore, if a const object has a constant initializer, we don't
413/// actually need to keep storage for it in the block; we'll just
414/// rematerialize it at the start of the block function. This is
415/// acceptable because we make no promises about address stability of
416/// captured variables.
417static llvm::Constant *tryCaptureAsConstant(CodeGenModule &CGM,
418 CodeGenFunction *CGF,
419 const VarDecl *var) {
420 // Return if this is a function parameter. We shouldn't try to
421 // rematerialize default arguments of function parameters.
422 if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(var))
423 return nullptr;
424
425 QualType type = var->getType();
426
427 // We can only do this if the variable is const.
428 if (!type.isConstQualified()) return nullptr;
429
430 // Furthermore, in C++ we have to worry about mutable fields:
431 // C++ [dcl.type.cv]p4:
432 // Except that any class member declared mutable can be
433 // modified, any attempt to modify a const object during its
434 // lifetime results in undefined behavior.
435 if (CGM.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && !isSafeForCXXConstantCapture(type))
436 return nullptr;
437
438 // If the variable doesn't have any initializer (shouldn't this be
439 // invalid?), it's not clear what we should do. Maybe capture as
440 // zero?
441 const Expr *init = var->getInit();
442 if (!init) return nullptr;
443
444 return ConstantEmitter(CGM, CGF).tryEmitAbstractForInitializer(*var);
445}

447/// Get the low bit of a nonzero character count. This is the
448/// alignment of the nth byte if the 0th byte is universally aligned.
449static CharUnits getLowBit(CharUnits v) {
450 return CharUnits::fromQuantity(v.getQuantity() & (~v.getQuantity() + 1));
451}
452
453static void initializeForBlockHeader(CodeGenModule &CGM, CGBlockInfo &info,
454 SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Type*> &elementTypes) {
455
456 assert(elementTypes.empty());
457 if (CGM.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
458 // The header is basically 'struct { int; int; generic void *;
459 // custom_fields; }'. Assert that struct is packed.
460 auto GenericAS =
461 CGM.getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_generic);
462 auto GenPtrAlign =
463 CharUnits::fromQuantity(CGM.getTarget().getPointerAlign(GenericAS) / 8);
464 auto GenPtrSize =
465 CharUnits::fromQuantity(CGM.getTarget().getPointerWidth(GenericAS) / 8);
466 assert(CGM.getIntSize() <= GenPtrSize);
467 assert(CGM.getIntAlign() <= GenPtrAlign);
468 assert((2 * CGM.getIntSize()).isMultipleOf(GenPtrAlign));
469 elementTypes.push_back(CGM.IntTy); /* total size */
470 elementTypes.push_back(CGM.IntTy); /* align */
471 elementTypes.push_back(
472 CGM.getOpenCLRuntime()
473 .getGenericVoidPointerType()); /* invoke function */
474 unsigned Offset =
475 2 * CGM.getIntSize().getQuantity() + GenPtrSize.getQuantity();
476 unsigned BlockAlign = GenPtrAlign.getQuantity();
477 if (auto *Helper =
478 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getTargetOpenCLBlockHelper()) {
479 for (auto I : Helper->getCustomFieldTypes()) /* custom fields */ {
480 // TargetOpenCLBlockHelp needs to make sure the struct is packed.
481 // If necessary, add padding fields to the custom fields.
482 unsigned Align = CGM.getDataLayout().getABITypeAlignment(I);
483 if (BlockAlign < Align)
484 BlockAlign = Align;
485 assert(Offset % Align == 0);
486 Offset += CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(I);
487 elementTypes.push_back(I);
488 }
489 }
490 info.BlockAlign = CharUnits::fromQuantity(BlockAlign);
491 info.BlockSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity(Offset);
492 } else {
493 // The header is basically 'struct { void *; int; int; void *; void *; }'.
494 // Assert that the struct is packed.
495 assert(CGM.getIntSize() <= CGM.getPointerSize());
496 assert(CGM.getIntAlign() <= CGM.getPointerAlign());
497 assert((2 * CGM.getIntSize()).isMultipleOf(CGM.getPointerAlign()));
498 info.BlockAlign = CGM.getPointerAlign();
499 info.BlockSize = 3 * CGM.getPointerSize() + 2 * CGM.getIntSize();
500 elementTypes.push_back(CGM.VoidPtrTy);
501 elementTypes.push_back(CGM.IntTy);
502 elementTypes.push_back(CGM.IntTy);
503 elementTypes.push_back(CGM.VoidPtrTy);
504 elementTypes.push_back(CGM.getBlockDescriptorType());
505 }
506}
507
508static QualType getCaptureFieldType(const CodeGenFunction &CGF,
509 const BlockDecl::Capture &CI) {
510 const VarDecl *VD = CI.getVariable();
511
512 // If the variable is captured by an enclosing block or lambda expression,
513 // use the type of the capture field.
514 if (CGF.BlockInfo && CI.isNested())
515 return CGF.BlockInfo->getCapture(VD).fieldType();
516 if (auto *FD = CGF.LambdaCaptureFields.lookup(VD))
517 return FD->getType();
518 // If the captured variable is a non-escaping __block variable, the field
519 // type is the reference type. If the variable is a __block variable that
520 // already has a reference type, the field type is the variable's type.
521 return VD->isNonEscapingByref() ?
522 CGF.getContext().getLValueReferenceType(VD->getType()) : VD->getType();
523}

525/// Compute the layout of the given block. Attempts to lay the block
526/// out with minimal space requirements.
527static void computeBlockInfo(CodeGenModule &CGM, CodeGenFunction *CGF,
528 CGBlockInfo &info) {
529 ASTContext &C = CGM.getContext();
530 const BlockDecl *block = info.getBlockDecl();
531
532 SmallVector<llvm::Type*, 8> elementTypes;
533 initializeForBlockHeader(CGM, info, elementTypes);
534 bool hasNonConstantCustomFields = false;
535 if (auto *OpenCLHelper =
536 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getTargetOpenCLBlockHelper())
537 hasNonConstantCustomFields =
538 !OpenCLHelper->areAllCustomFieldValuesConstant(info);
539 if (!block->hasCaptures() && !hasNonConstantCustomFields) {
540 info.StructureType =
541 llvm::StructType::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), elementTypes, true);
542 info.CanBeGlobal = true;
543 return;
544 }
545 else if (C.getLangOpts().ObjC &&
546 CGM.getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::NonGC)
547 info.HasCapturedVariableLayout = true;
548
549 // Collect the layout chunks.
550 SmallVector<BlockLayoutChunk, 16> layout;
551 layout.reserve(block->capturesCXXThis() +
552 (block->capture_end() - block->capture_begin()));
553
554 CharUnits maxFieldAlign;
555
556 // First, 'this'.
557 if (block->capturesCXXThis()) {
558 assert(CGF && CGF->CurFuncDecl && isa<CXXMethodDecl>(CGF->CurFuncDecl) &&
559 "Can't capture 'this' outside a method");
560 QualType thisType = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(CGF->CurFuncDecl)->getThisType();
561
562 // Theoretically, this could be in a different address space, so
563 // don't assume standard pointer size/align.
564 llvm::Type *llvmType = CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(thisType);
565 std::pair<CharUnits,CharUnits> tinfo
566 = CGM.getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(thisType);
567 maxFieldAlign = std::max(maxFieldAlign, tinfo.second);
568
569 layout.push_back(BlockLayoutChunk(tinfo.second, tinfo.first,
570 Qualifiers::OCL_None,
571 nullptr, llvmType, thisType));
572 }
573
574 // Next, all the block captures.
575 for (const auto &CI : block->captures()) {
576 const VarDecl *variable = CI.getVariable();
577
578 if (CI.isEscapingByref()) {
579 // We have to copy/dispose of the __block reference.
580 info.NeedsCopyDispose = true;
581
582 // Just use void* instead of a pointer to the byref type.
583 CharUnits align = CGM.getPointerAlign();
584 maxFieldAlign = std::max(maxFieldAlign, align);
585
586 // Since a __block variable cannot be captured by lambdas, its type and
587 // the capture field type should always match.
588 assert(getCaptureFieldType(*CGF, CI) == variable->getType() &&
589 "capture type differs from the variable type");
590 layout.push_back(BlockLayoutChunk(align, CGM.getPointerSize(),
591 Qualifiers::OCL_None, &CI,
592 CGM.VoidPtrTy, variable->getType()));
593 continue;
594 }
595
596 // Otherwise, build a layout chunk with the size and alignment of
597 // the declaration.
598 if (llvm::Constant *constant = tryCaptureAsConstant(CGM, CGF, variable)) {
599 info.Captures[variable] = CGBlockInfo::Capture::makeConstant(constant);
600 continue;
601 }
602
603 QualType VT = getCaptureFieldType(*CGF, CI);
604
605 // If we have a lifetime qualifier, honor it for capture purposes.
606 // That includes *not* copying it if it's __unsafe_unretained.
607 Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime lifetime = VT.getObjCLifetime();
608 if (lifetime) {
609 switch (lifetime) {
610 case Qualifiers::OCL_None: llvm_unreachable("impossible");
611 case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
612 case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
613 break;
614
615 case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
616 case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
617 info.NeedsCopyDispose = true;
618 }
619
620 // Block pointers require copy/dispose. So do Objective-C pointers.
621 } else if (VT->isObjCRetainableType()) {
622 // But honor the inert __unsafe_unretained qualifier, which doesn't
623 // actually make it into the type system.
624 if (VT->isObjCInertUnsafeUnretainedType()) {
625 lifetime = Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone;
626 } else {
627 info.NeedsCopyDispose = true;
628 // used for mrr below.
629 lifetime = Qualifiers::OCL_Strong;
630 }
631
632 // So do types that require non-trivial copy construction.
633 } else if (CI.hasCopyExpr()) {
634 info.NeedsCopyDispose = true;
635 info.HasCXXObject = true;
636 if (!VT->getAsCXXRecordDecl()->isExternallyVisible())
637 info.CapturesNonExternalType = true;
638
639 // So do C structs that require non-trivial copy construction or
640 // destruction.
641 } else if (VT.isNonTrivialToPrimitiveCopy() == QualType::PCK_Struct ||
642 VT.isDestructedType() == QualType::DK_nontrivial_c_struct) {
643 info.NeedsCopyDispose = true;
644
645 // And so do types with destructors.
646 } else if (CGM.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
647 if (const CXXRecordDecl *record = VT->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
648 if (!record->hasTrivialDestructor()) {
649 info.HasCXXObject = true;
650 info.NeedsCopyDispose = true;
651 if (!record->isExternallyVisible())
652 info.CapturesNonExternalType = true;
653 }
654 }
655 }
656
657 CharUnits size = C.getTypeSizeInChars(VT);
658 CharUnits align = C.getDeclAlign(variable);
659
660 maxFieldAlign = std::max(maxFieldAlign, align);
661
662 llvm::Type *llvmType =
663 CGM.getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(VT);
664
665 layout.push_back(
666 BlockLayoutChunk(align, size, lifetime, &CI, llvmType, VT));
667 }
668
669 // If that was everything, we're done here.
670 if (layout.empty()) {
671 info.StructureType =
672 llvm::StructType::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), elementTypes, true);
673 info.CanBeGlobal = true;
674 return;
675 }
676
677 // Sort the layout by alignment. We have to use a stable sort here
678 // to get reproducible results. There should probably be an
679 // llvm::array_pod_stable_sort.
680 llvm::stable_sort(layout);
681
682 // Needed for blocks layout info.
683 info.BlockHeaderForcedGapOffset = info.BlockSize;
684 info.BlockHeaderForcedGapSize = CharUnits::Zero();
685
686 CharUnits &blockSize = info.BlockSize;
687 info.BlockAlign = std::max(maxFieldAlign, info.BlockAlign);
688
689 // Assuming that the first byte in the header is maximally aligned,
690 // get the alignment of the first byte following the header.
691 CharUnits endAlign = getLowBit(blockSize);
692
693 // If the end of the header isn't satisfactorily aligned for the
694 // maximum thing, look for things that are okay with the header-end
695 // alignment, and keep appending them until we get something that's
696 // aligned right. This algorithm is only guaranteed optimal if
697 // that condition is satisfied at some point; otherwise we can get
698 // things like:
699 // header // next byte has alignment 4
700 // something_with_size_5; // next byte has alignment 1
701 // something_with_alignment_8;
702 // which has 7 bytes of padding, as opposed to the naive solution
703 // which might have less (?).
704 if (endAlign < maxFieldAlign) {
705 SmallVectorImpl<BlockLayoutChunk>::iterator
706 li = layout.begin() + 1, le = layout.end();
707
708 // Look for something that the header end is already
709 // satisfactorily aligned for.
710 for (; li != le && endAlign < li->Alignment; ++li)
711 ;
712
713 // If we found something that's naturally aligned for the end of
714 // the header, keep adding things...
715 if (li != le) {
716 SmallVectorImpl<BlockLayoutChunk>::iterator first = li;
717 for (; li != le; ++li) {
718 assert(endAlign >= li->Alignment);
719
720 li->setIndex(info, elementTypes.size(), blockSize);
721 elementTypes.push_back(li->Type);
722 blockSize += li->Size;
723 endAlign = getLowBit(blockSize);
724
725 // ...until we get to the alignment of the maximum field.
726 if (endAlign >= maxFieldAlign) {
727 break;
728 }
729 }
730 // Don't re-append everything we just appended.
731 layout.erase(first, li);
732 }
733 }
734
735 assert(endAlign == getLowBit(blockSize));
736
737 // At this point, we just have to add padding if the end align still
738 // isn't aligned right.
739 if (endAlign < maxFieldAlign) {
740 CharUnits newBlockSize = blockSize.alignTo(maxFieldAlign);
741 CharUnits padding = newBlockSize - blockSize;
742
743 // If we haven't yet added any fields, remember that there was an
744 // initial gap; this need to go into the block layout bit map.
745 if (blockSize == info.BlockHeaderForcedGapOffset) {
746 info.BlockHeaderForcedGapSize = padding;
747 }
748
749 elementTypes.push_back(llvm::ArrayType::get(CGM.Int8Ty,
750 padding.getQuantity()));
751 blockSize = newBlockSize;
752 endAlign = getLowBit(blockSize); // might be > maxFieldAlign
753 }
754
755 assert(endAlign >= maxFieldAlign);
756 assert(endAlign == getLowBit(blockSize));
757 // Slam everything else on now. This works because they have
758 // strictly decreasing alignment and we expect that size is always a
759 // multiple of alignment.
760 for (SmallVectorImpl<BlockLayoutChunk>::iterator
761 li = layout.begin(), le = layout.end(); li != le; ++li) {
762 if (endAlign < li->Alignment) {
763 // size may not be multiple of alignment. This can only happen with
764 // an over-aligned variable. We will be adding a padding field to
765 // make the size be multiple of alignment.
766 CharUnits padding = li->Alignment - endAlign;
767 elementTypes.push_back(llvm::ArrayType::get(CGM.Int8Ty,
768 padding.getQuantity()));
769 blockSize += padding;
770 endAlign = getLowBit(blockSize);
771 }
772 assert(endAlign >= li->Alignment);
773 li->setIndex(info, elementTypes.size(), blockSize);
774 elementTypes.push_back(li->Type);
775 blockSize += li->Size;
776 endAlign = getLowBit(blockSize);
777 }
778
779 info.StructureType =
780 llvm::StructType::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), elementTypes, true);
781}

783/// Enter the scope of a block. This should be run at the entrance to
784/// a full-expression so that the block's cleanups are pushed at the
785/// right place in the stack.
786static void enterBlockScope(CodeGenFunction &CGF, BlockDecl *block) {
787 assert(CGF.HaveInsertPoint());
788
789 // Allocate the block info and place it at the head of the list.
790 CGBlockInfo &blockInfo =
791 *new CGBlockInfo(block, CGF.CurFn->getName());
792 blockInfo.NextBlockInfo = CGF.FirstBlockInfo;
793 CGF.FirstBlockInfo = &blockInfo;
794
795 // Compute information about the layout, etc., of this block,
796 // pushing cleanups as necessary.
797 computeBlockInfo(CGF.CGM, &CGF, blockInfo);
798
799 // Nothing else to do if it can be global.
800 if (blockInfo.CanBeGlobal) return;
801
802 // Make the allocation for the block.
803 blockInfo.LocalAddress = CGF.CreateTempAlloca(blockInfo.StructureType,
804 blockInfo.BlockAlign, "block");
805
806 // If there are cleanups to emit, enter them (but inactive).
807 if (!blockInfo.NeedsCopyDispose) return;
808
809 // Walk through the captures (in order) and find the ones not
810 // captured by constant.
811 for (const auto &CI : block->captures()) {
812 // Ignore __block captures; there's nothing special in the
813 // on-stack block that we need to do for them.
814 if (CI.isByRef()) continue;
815
816 // Ignore variables that are constant-captured.
817 const VarDecl *variable = CI.getVariable();
818 CGBlockInfo::Capture &capture = blockInfo.getCapture(variable);
819 if (capture.isConstant()) continue;
820
821 // Ignore objects that aren't destructed.
822 QualType VT = getCaptureFieldType(CGF, CI);
823 QualType::DestructionKind dtorKind = VT.isDestructedType();
824 if (dtorKind == QualType::DK_none) continue;
825
826 CodeGenFunction::Destroyer *destroyer;
827
828 // Block captures count as local values and have imprecise semantics.
829 // They also can't be arrays, so need to worry about that.
830 //
831 // For const-qualified captures, emit clang.arc.use to ensure the captured
832 // object doesn't get released while we are still depending on its validity
833 // within the block.
834 if (VT.isConstQualified() &&
835 VT.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Strong &&
836 CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel != 0) {
837 assert(CGF.CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount &&
838 "expected ObjC ARC to be enabled");
839 destroyer = CodeGenFunction::emitARCIntrinsicUse;
840 } else if (dtorKind == QualType::DK_objc_strong_lifetime) {
841 destroyer = CodeGenFunction::destroyARCStrongImprecise;
842 } else {
843 destroyer = CGF.getDestroyer(dtorKind);
844 }
845
846 // GEP down to the address.
847 Address addr =
848 CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(blockInfo.LocalAddress, capture.getIndex());
849
850 // We can use that GEP as the dominating IP.
851 if (!blockInfo.DominatingIP)
852 blockInfo.DominatingIP = cast<llvm::Instruction>(addr.getPointer());
853
854 CleanupKind cleanupKind = InactiveNormalCleanup;
855 bool useArrayEHCleanup = CGF.needsEHCleanup(dtorKind);
856 if (useArrayEHCleanup)
857 cleanupKind = InactiveNormalAndEHCleanup;
858
859 CGF.pushDestroy(cleanupKind, addr, VT,
860 destroyer, useArrayEHCleanup);
861
862 // Remember where that cleanup was.
863 capture.setCleanup(CGF.EHStack.stable_begin());
864 }
865}
866
867/// Enter a full-expression with a non-trivial number of objects to
868/// clean up. This is in this file because, at the moment, the only
869/// kind of cleanup object is a BlockDecl*.
870void CodeGenFunction::enterNonTrivialFullExpression(const FullExpr *E) {
871 if (const auto EWC = dyn_cast<ExprWithCleanups>(E)) {
872 assert(EWC->getNumObjects() != 0);
873 for (const ExprWithCleanups::CleanupObject &C : EWC->getObjects())
874 enterBlockScope(*this, C);
875 }
876}
877
878/// Find the layout for the given block in a linked list and remove it.
879static CGBlockInfo *findAndRemoveBlockInfo(CGBlockInfo **head,
880 const BlockDecl *block) {
881 while (true) {
882 assert(head && *head);
883 CGBlockInfo *cur = *head;
884
885 // If this is the block we're looking for, splice it out of the list.
886 if (cur->getBlockDecl() == block) {
887 *head = cur->NextBlockInfo;
888 return cur;
889 }
890
891 head = &cur->NextBlockInfo;
892 }
893}
894
895/// Destroy a chain of block layouts.
896void CodeGenFunction::destroyBlockInfos(CGBlockInfo *head) {
897 assert(head && "destroying an empty chain");
898 do {
899 CGBlockInfo *cur = head;
900 head = cur->NextBlockInfo;
901 delete cur;
902 } while (head != nullptr);
903}
904
905/// Emit a block literal expression in the current function.
906llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitBlockLiteral(const BlockExpr *blockExpr) {
907 // If the block has no captures, we won't have a pre-computed
908 // layout for it.
909 if (!blockExpr->getBlockDecl()->hasCaptures()) {
910 // The block literal is emitted as a global variable, and the block invoke
911 // function has to be extracted from its initializer.
912 if (llvm::Constant *Block = CGM.getAddrOfGlobalBlockIfEmitted(blockExpr)) {
913 return Block;
914 }
915 CGBlockInfo blockInfo(blockExpr->getBlockDecl(), CurFn->getName());
916 computeBlockInfo(CGM, this, blockInfo);
917 blockInfo.BlockExpression = blockExpr;
918 return EmitBlockLiteral(blockInfo);
919 }
920
921 // Find the block info for this block and take ownership of it.
922 std::unique_ptr<CGBlockInfo> blockInfo;
923 blockInfo.reset(findAndRemoveBlockInfo(&FirstBlockInfo,
924 blockExpr->getBlockDecl()));
925
926 blockInfo->BlockExpression = blockExpr;
927 return EmitBlockLiteral(*blockInfo);
928}
929
930llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitBlockLiteral(const CGBlockInfo &blockInfo) {
931 bool IsOpenCL = CGM.getContext().getLangOpts().OpenCL;
932 auto GenVoidPtrTy =
933 IsOpenCL ? CGM.getOpenCLRuntime().getGenericVoidPointerType() : VoidPtrTy;
934 LangAS GenVoidPtrAddr = IsOpenCL ? LangAS::opencl_generic : LangAS::Default;
935 auto GenVoidPtrSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity(
936 CGM.getTarget().getPointerWidth(
937 CGM.getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(GenVoidPtrAddr)) /
938 8);
939 // Using the computed layout, generate the actual block function.
940 bool isLambdaConv = blockInfo.getBlockDecl()->isConversionFromLambda();
941 CodeGenFunction BlockCGF{CGM, true};
942 BlockCGF.SanOpts = SanOpts;
943 auto *InvokeFn = BlockCGF.GenerateBlockFunction(
944 CurGD, blockInfo, LocalDeclMap, isLambdaConv, blockInfo.CanBeGlobal);
945 auto *blockFn = llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerCast(InvokeFn, GenVoidPtrTy);
946
947 // If there is nothing to capture, we can emit this as a global block.
948 if (blockInfo.CanBeGlobal)
949 return CGM.getAddrOfGlobalBlockIfEmitted(blockInfo.BlockExpression);
950
951 // Otherwise, we have to emit this as a local block.
952
953 Address blockAddr = blockInfo.LocalAddress;
954 assert(blockAddr.isValid() && "block has no address!");
955
956 llvm::Constant *isa;
957 llvm::Constant *descriptor;
958 BlockFlags flags;
959 if (!IsOpenCL) {
960 // If the block is non-escaping, set field 'isa 'to NSConcreteGlobalBlock
961 // and set the BLOCK_IS_GLOBAL bit of field 'flags'. Copying a non-escaping
962 // block just returns the original block and releasing it is a no-op.
963 llvm::Constant *blockISA = blockInfo.getBlockDecl()->doesNotEscape()
964 ? CGM.getNSConcreteGlobalBlock()
965 : CGM.getNSConcreteStackBlock();
966 isa = llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(blockISA, VoidPtrTy);
967
968 // Build the block descriptor.
969 descriptor = buildBlockDescriptor(CGM, blockInfo);
970
971 // Compute the initial on-stack block flags.
972 flags = BLOCK_HAS_SIGNATURE;
973 if (blockInfo.HasCapturedVariableLayout)
974 flags |= BLOCK_HAS_EXTENDED_LAYOUT;
975 if (blockInfo.needsCopyDisposeHelpers())
976 flags |= BLOCK_HAS_COPY_DISPOSE;
977 if (blockInfo.HasCXXObject)
978 flags |= BLOCK_HAS_CXX_OBJ;
979 if (blockInfo.UsesStret)
980 flags |= BLOCK_USE_STRET;
981 if (blockInfo.getBlockDecl()->doesNotEscape())
982 flags |= BLOCK_IS_NOESCAPE | BLOCK_IS_GLOBAL;
983 }
984
985 auto projectField = [&](unsigned index, const Twine &name) -> Address {
986 return Builder.CreateStructGEP(blockAddr, index, name);
987 };
988 auto storeField = [&](llvm::Value *value, unsigned index, const Twine &name) {
989 Builder.CreateStore(value, projectField(index, name));
990 };
991
992 // Initialize the block header.
993 {
994 // We assume all the header fields are densely packed.
995 unsigned index = 0;
996 CharUnits offset;
997 auto addHeaderField = [&](llvm::Value *value, CharUnits size,
998 const Twine &name) {
999 storeField(value, index, name);
1000 offset += size;
1001 index++;
1002 };
1003
1004 if (!IsOpenCL) {
1005 addHeaderField(isa, getPointerSize(), "block.isa");
1006 addHeaderField(llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy, flags.getBitMask()),
1007 getIntSize(), "block.flags");
1008 addHeaderField(llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy, 0), getIntSize(),
1009 "block.reserved");
1010 } else {
1011 addHeaderField(
1012 llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy, blockInfo.BlockSize.getQuantity()),
1013 getIntSize(), "block.size");
1014 addHeaderField(
1015 llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy, blockInfo.BlockAlign.getQuantity()),
1016 getIntSize(), "block.align");
1017 }
1018 addHeaderField(blockFn, GenVoidPtrSize, "block.invoke");
1019 if (!IsOpenCL)
1020 addHeaderField(descriptor, getPointerSize(), "block.descriptor");
1021 else if (auto *Helper =
1022 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getTargetOpenCLBlockHelper()) {
1023 for (auto I : Helper->getCustomFieldValues(*this, blockInfo)) {
1024 addHeaderField(
1025 I.first,
1026 CharUnits::fromQuantity(
1027 CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(I.first->getType())),
1028 I.second);
1029 }
1030 }
1031 }
1032
1033 // Finally, capture all the values into the block.
1034 const BlockDecl *blockDecl = blockInfo.getBlockDecl();
1035
1036 // First, 'this'.
1037 if (blockDecl->capturesCXXThis()) {
1038 Address addr =
1039 projectField(blockInfo.CXXThisIndex, "block.captured-this.addr");
1040 Builder.CreateStore(LoadCXXThis(), addr);
1041 }
1042
1043 // Next, captured variables.
1044 for (const auto &CI : blockDecl->captures()) {
1045 const VarDecl *variable = CI.getVariable();
1046 const CGBlockInfo::Capture &capture = blockInfo.getCapture(variable);
1047
1048 // Ignore constant captures.
1049 if (capture.isConstant()) continue;
1050
1051 QualType type = capture.fieldType();
1052
1053 // This will be a [[type]]*, except that a byref entry will just be
1054 // an i8**.
1055 Address blockField = projectField(capture.getIndex(), "block.captured");
1056
1057 // Compute the address of the thing we're going to move into the
1058 // block literal.
1059 Address src = Address::invalid();
1060
1061 if (blockDecl->isConversionFromLambda()) {
1062 // The lambda capture in a lambda's conversion-to-block-pointer is
1063 // special; we'll simply emit it directly.
1064 src = Address::invalid();
1065 } else if (CI.isEscapingByref()) {
1066 if (BlockInfo && CI.isNested()) {
1067 // We need to use the capture from the enclosing block.
1068 const CGBlockInfo::Capture &enclosingCapture =
1069 BlockInfo->getCapture(variable);
1070
1071 // This is a [[type]]*, except that a byref entry will just be an i8**.
1072 src = Builder.CreateStructGEP(LoadBlockStruct(),
1073 enclosingCapture.getIndex(),
1074 "block.capture.addr");
1075 } else {
1076 auto I = LocalDeclMap.find(variable);
1077 assert(I != LocalDeclMap.end());
1078 src = I->second;
1079 }
1080 } else {
1081 DeclRefExpr declRef(getContext(), const_cast<VarDecl *>(variable),
1082 /*RefersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture*/ CI.isNested(),
1083 type.getNonReferenceType(), VK_LValue,
1084 SourceLocation());
1085 src = EmitDeclRefLValue(&declRef).getAddress();
1086 };
1087
1088 // For byrefs, we just write the pointer to the byref struct into
1089 // the block field. There's no need to chase the forwarding
1090 // pointer at this point, since we're building something that will
1091 // live a shorter life than the stack byref anyway.
1092 if (CI.isEscapingByref()) {
1093 // Get a void* that points to the byref struct.
1094 llvm::Value *byrefPointer;
1095 if (CI.isNested())
1096 byrefPointer = Builder.CreateLoad(src, "byref.capture");
1097 else
1098 byrefPointer =
1099 Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(src.getPointer(),
1100 VoidPtrTy);
1101
1102 // Write that void* into the capture field.
1103 Builder.CreateStore(byrefPointer, blockField);
1104
1105 // If we have a copy constructor, evaluate that into the block field.
1106 } else if (const Expr *copyExpr = CI.getCopyExpr()) {
1107 if (blockDecl->isConversionFromLambda()) {
1108 // If we have a lambda conversion, emit the expression
1109 // directly into the block instead.
1110 AggValueSlot Slot =
1111 AggValueSlot::forAddr(blockField, Qualifiers(),
1112 AggValueSlot::IsDestructed,
1113 AggValueSlot::DoesNotNeedGCBarriers,
1114 AggValueSlot::IsNotAliased,
1115 AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap);
1116 EmitAggExpr(copyExpr, Slot);
1117 } else {
1118 EmitSynthesizedCXXCopyCtor(blockField, src, copyExpr);
1119 }
1120
1121 // If it's a reference variable, copy the reference into the block field.
1122 } else if (type->isReferenceType()) {
1123 Builder.CreateStore(src.getPointer(), blockField);
1124
1125 // If type is const-qualified, copy the value into the block field.
1126 } else if (type.isConstQualified() &&
1127 type.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Strong &&
1128 CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel != 0) {
1129 llvm::Value *value = Builder.CreateLoad(src, "captured");
1130 Builder.CreateStore(value, blockField);
1131
1132 // If this is an ARC __strong block-pointer variable, don't do a
1133 // block copy.
1134 //
1135 // TODO: this can be generalized into the normal initialization logic:
1136 // we should never need to do a block-copy when initializing a local
1137 // variable, because the local variable's lifetime should be strictly
1138 // contained within the stack block's.
1139 } else if (type.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Strong &&
1140 type->isBlockPointerType()) {
1141 // Load the block and do a simple retain.
1142 llvm::Value *value = Builder.CreateLoad(src, "block.captured_block");
1143 value = EmitARCRetainNonBlock(value);
1144
1145 // Do a primitive store to the block field.
1146 Builder.CreateStore(value, blockField);
1147
1148 // Otherwise, fake up a POD copy into the block field.
1149 } else {
1150 // Fake up a new variable so that EmitScalarInit doesn't think
1151 // we're referring to the variable in its own initializer.
1152 ImplicitParamDecl BlockFieldPseudoVar(getContext(), type,
1153 ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
1154
1155 // We use one of these or the other depending on whether the
1156 // reference is nested.
1157 DeclRefExpr declRef(getContext(), const_cast<VarDecl *>(variable),
1158 /*RefersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture*/ CI.isNested(),
1159 type, VK_LValue, SourceLocation());
1160
1161 ImplicitCastExpr l2r(ImplicitCastExpr::OnStack, type, CK_LValueToRValue,
1162 &declRef, VK_RValue);
1163 // FIXME: Pass a specific location for the expr init so that the store is
1164 // attributed to a reasonable location - otherwise it may be attributed to
1165 // locations of subexpressions in the initialization.
1166 EmitExprAsInit(&l2r, &BlockFieldPseudoVar,
1167 MakeAddrLValue(blockField, type, AlignmentSource::Decl),
1168 /*captured by init*/ false);
1169 }
1170
1171 // Activate the cleanup if layout pushed one.
1172 if (!CI.isByRef()) {
1173 EHScopeStack::stable_iterator cleanup = capture.getCleanup();
1174 if (cleanup.isValid())
1175 ActivateCleanupBlock(cleanup, blockInfo.DominatingIP);
1176 }
1177 }
1178
1179 // Cast to the converted block-pointer type, which happens (somewhat
1180 // unfortunately) to be a pointer to function type.
1181 llvm::Value *result = Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
1182 blockAddr.getPointer(), ConvertType(blockInfo.getBlockExpr()->getType()));
1183
1184 if (IsOpenCL) {
1185 CGM.getOpenCLRuntime().recordBlockInfo(blockInfo.BlockExpression, InvokeFn,
1186 result);
1187 }
1188
1189 return result;
1190}

1193llvm::Type *CodeGenModule::getBlockDescriptorType() {
1194 if (BlockDescriptorType)
1195 return BlockDescriptorType;
1196
1197 llvm::Type *UnsignedLongTy =
1198 getTypes().ConvertType(getContext().UnsignedLongTy);
1199
1200 // struct __block_descriptor {
1201 // unsigned long reserved;
1202 // unsigned long block_size;
1203 //
1204 // // later, the following will be added
1205 //
1206 // struct {
1207 // void (*copyHelper)();
1208 // void (*copyHelper)();
1209 // } helpers; // !!! optional
1210 //
1211 // const char *signature; // the block signature
1212 // const char *layout; // reserved
1213 // };
1214 BlockDescriptorType = llvm::StructType::create(
1215 "struct.__block_descriptor", UnsignedLongTy, UnsignedLongTy);
1216
1217 // Now form a pointer to that.
1218 unsigned AddrSpace = getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
1219 if (getLangOpts().OpenCL)
1220 AddrSpace = getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_constant);
1221 BlockDescriptorType = llvm::PointerType::get(BlockDescriptorType, AddrSpace);
1222 return BlockDescriptorType;
1223}
1224
1225llvm::Type *CodeGenModule::getGenericBlockLiteralType() {
1226 if (GenericBlockLiteralType)
1227 return GenericBlockLiteralType;
1228
1229 llvm::Type *BlockDescPtrTy = getBlockDescriptorType();
1230
1231 if (getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
1232 // struct __opencl_block_literal_generic {
1233 // int __size;
1234 // int __align;
1235 // __generic void *__invoke;
1236 // /* custom fields */
1237 // };
1238 SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 8> StructFields(
1239 {IntTy, IntTy, getOpenCLRuntime().getGenericVoidPointerType()});
1240 if (auto *Helper = getTargetCodeGenInfo().getTargetOpenCLBlockHelper()) {
1241 for (auto I : Helper->getCustomFieldTypes())
1242 StructFields.push_back(I);
1243 }
1244 GenericBlockLiteralType = llvm::StructType::create(
1245 StructFields, "struct.__opencl_block_literal_generic");
1246 } else {
1247 // struct __block_literal_generic {
1248 // void *__isa;
1249 // int __flags;
1250 // int __reserved;
1251 // void (*__invoke)(void *);
1252 // struct __block_descriptor *__descriptor;
1253 // };
1254 GenericBlockLiteralType =
1255 llvm::StructType::create("struct.__block_literal_generic", VoidPtrTy,
1256 IntTy, IntTy, VoidPtrTy, BlockDescPtrTy);
1257 }
1258
1259 return GenericBlockLiteralType;
1260}
1261
1262RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitBlockCallExpr(const CallExpr *E,
1263 ReturnValueSlot ReturnValue) {
1264 const BlockPointerType *BPT =
1265 E->getCallee()->getType()->getAs<BlockPointerType>();
1266 llvm::Value *BlockPtr = EmitScalarExpr(E->getCallee());
1267 llvm::Type *GenBlockTy = CGM.getGenericBlockLiteralType();
1268 llvm::Value *Func = nullptr;
1269 QualType FnType = BPT->getPointeeType();
1270 ASTContext &Ctx = getContext();
1271 CallArgList Args;
1272
1273 if (getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
1274 // For OpenCL, BlockPtr is already casted to generic block literal.
1275
1276 // First argument of a block call is a generic block literal casted to
1277 // generic void pointer, i.e. i8 addrspace(4)*
1278 llvm::Value *BlockDescriptor = Builder.CreatePointerCast(
1279 BlockPtr, CGM.getOpenCLRuntime().getGenericVoidPointerType());
1280 QualType VoidPtrQualTy = Ctx.getPointerType(
1281 Ctx.getAddrSpaceQualType(Ctx.VoidTy, LangAS::opencl_generic));
1282 Args.add(RValue::get(BlockDescriptor), VoidPtrQualTy);
1283 // And the rest of the arguments.
1284 EmitCallArgs(Args, FnType->getAs<FunctionProtoType>(), E->arguments());
1285
1286 // We *can* call the block directly unless it is a function argument.
1287 if (!isa<ParmVarDecl>(E->getCalleeDecl()))
1288 Func = CGM.getOpenCLRuntime().getInvokeFunction(E->getCallee());
1289 else {
1290 llvm::Value *FuncPtr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(GenBlockTy, BlockPtr, 2);
1291 Func = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(FuncPtr, getPointerAlign());
1292 }
1293 } else {
1294 // Bitcast the block literal to a generic block literal.
1295 BlockPtr = Builder.CreatePointerCast(
1296 BlockPtr, llvm::PointerType::get(GenBlockTy, 0), "block.literal");
1297 // Get pointer to the block invoke function
1298 llvm::Value *FuncPtr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(GenBlockTy, BlockPtr, 3);
1299
1300 // First argument is a block literal casted to a void pointer
1301 BlockPtr = Builder.CreatePointerCast(BlockPtr, VoidPtrTy);
1302 Args.add(RValue::get(BlockPtr), Ctx.VoidPtrTy);
1303 // And the rest of the arguments.
1304 EmitCallArgs(Args, FnType->getAs<FunctionProtoType>(), E->arguments());
1305
1306 // Load the function.
1307 Func = Builder.CreateAlignedLoad(FuncPtr, getPointerAlign());
1308 }
1309
1310 const FunctionType *FuncTy = FnType->castAs<FunctionType>();
1311 const CGFunctionInfo &FnInfo =
1312 CGM.getTypes().arrangeBlockFunctionCall(Args, FuncTy);
1313
1314 // Cast the function pointer to the right type.
1315 llvm::Type *BlockFTy = CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(FnInfo);
1316
1317 llvm::Type *BlockFTyPtr = llvm::PointerType::get(BlockFTy, CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS());
1318 Func = Builder.CreatePointerCast(Func, BlockFTyPtr);
1319
1320 // Prepare the callee.
1321 CGCallee Callee(CGCalleeInfo(), Func);
1322
1323 // And call the block.
1324 return EmitCall(FnInfo, Callee, ReturnValue, Args);
1325}
1326
1327Address CodeGenFunction::GetAddrOfBlockDecl(const VarDecl *variable) {
1328 assert(BlockInfo && "evaluating block ref without block information?");
1329 const CGBlockInfo::Capture &capture = BlockInfo->getCapture(variable);
1330
1331 // Handle constant captures.
1332 if (capture.isConstant()) return LocalDeclMap.find(variable)->second;
1333
1334 Address addr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(LoadBlockStruct(), capture.getIndex(),
1335 "block.capture.addr");
1336
1337 if (variable->isEscapingByref()) {
1338 // addr should be a void** right now. Load, then cast the result
1339 // to byref*.
1340
1341 auto &byrefInfo = getBlockByrefInfo(variable);
1342 addr = Address(Builder.CreateLoad(addr), byrefInfo.ByrefAlignment);
1343
1344 auto byrefPointerType = llvm::PointerType::get(byrefInfo.Type,
1345 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS());
1346 addr = Builder.CreateBitCast(addr, byrefPointerType, "byref.addr");
1347
1348 addr = emitBlockByrefAddress(addr, byrefInfo, /*follow*/ true,
1349 variable->getName());
1350 }
1351
1352 assert((!variable->isNonEscapingByref() ||
1353 capture.fieldType()->isReferenceType()) &&
1354 "the capture field of a non-escaping variable should have a "
1355 "reference type");
1356 if (capture.fieldType()->isReferenceType())
1357 addr = EmitLoadOfReference(MakeAddrLValue(addr, capture.fieldType()));
1358
1359 return addr;
1360}

1362void CodeGenModule::setAddrOfGlobalBlock(const BlockExpr *BE,
1363 llvm::Constant *Addr) {
1364 bool Ok = EmittedGlobalBlocks.insert(std::make_pair(BE, Addr)).second;
1365 (void)Ok;
1366 assert(Ok && "Trying to replace an already-existing global block!");
1367}
1368
1369llvm::Constant *
1370CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfGlobalBlock(const BlockExpr *BE,
1371 StringRef Name) {
1372 if (llvm::Constant *Block = getAddrOfGlobalBlockIfEmitted(BE))
1373 return Block;
1374
1375 CGBlockInfo blockInfo(BE->getBlockDecl(), Name);
1376 blockInfo.BlockExpression = BE;
1377
1378 // Compute information about the layout, etc., of this block.
1379 computeBlockInfo(*this, nullptr, blockInfo);
1380
1381 // Using that metadata, generate the actual block function.
1382 {
1383 CodeGenFunction::DeclMapTy LocalDeclMap;
1384 CodeGenFunction(*this).GenerateBlockFunction(
1385 GlobalDecl(), blockInfo, LocalDeclMap,
1386 /*IsLambdaConversionToBlock*/ false, /*BuildGlobalBlock*/ true);
1387 }
1388
1389 return getAddrOfGlobalBlockIfEmitted(BE);
1390}
1391
1392static llvm::Constant *buildGlobalBlock(CodeGenModule &CGM,
1393 const CGBlockInfo &blockInfo,
1394 llvm::Constant *blockFn) {
1395 assert(blockInfo.CanBeGlobal);
1396 // Callers should detect this case on their own: calling this function
1397 // generally requires computing layout information, which is a waste of time
1398 // if we've already emitted this block.
1399 assert(!CGM.getAddrOfGlobalBlockIfEmitted(blockInfo.BlockExpression) &&
1400 "Refusing to re-emit a global block.");
1401
1402 // Generate the constants for the block literal initializer.
1403 ConstantInitBuilder builder(CGM);
1404 auto fields = builder.beginStruct();
1405
1406 bool IsOpenCL = CGM.getLangOpts().OpenCL;
1407 bool IsWindows = CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isOSWindows();
1408 if (!IsOpenCL) {
1409 // isa
1410 if (IsWindows)
1411 fields.addNullPointer(CGM.Int8PtrPtrTy);
1412 else
1413 fields.add(CGM.getNSConcreteGlobalBlock());
1414
1415 // __flags
1416 BlockFlags flags = BLOCK_IS_GLOBAL | BLOCK_HAS_SIGNATURE;
1417 if (blockInfo.UsesStret)
1418 flags |= BLOCK_USE_STRET;
1419
1420 fields.addInt(CGM.IntTy, flags.getBitMask());
1421
1422 // Reserved
1423 fields.addInt(CGM.IntTy, 0);
1424 } else {
1425 fields.addInt(CGM.IntTy, blockInfo.BlockSize.getQuantity());
1426 fields.addInt(CGM.IntTy, blockInfo.BlockAlign.getQuantity());
1427 }
1428
1429 // Function
1430 fields.add(blockFn);
1431
1432 if (!IsOpenCL) {
1433 // Descriptor
1434 fields.add(buildBlockDescriptor(CGM, blockInfo));
1435 } else if (auto *Helper =
1436 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getTargetOpenCLBlockHelper()) {
1437 for (auto I : Helper->getCustomFieldValues(CGM, blockInfo)) {
1438 fields.add(I);
1439 }
1440 }
1441
1442 unsigned AddrSpace = 0;
1443 if (CGM.getContext().getLangOpts().OpenCL)
1444 AddrSpace = CGM.getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_global);
1445
1446 llvm::Constant *literal = fields.finishAndCreateGlobal(
1447 "__block_literal_global", blockInfo.BlockAlign,
1448 /*constant*/ !IsWindows, llvm::GlobalVariable::InternalLinkage, AddrSpace);
1449
1450 // Windows does not allow globals to be initialised to point to globals in
1451 // different DLLs. Any such variables must run code to initialise them.
1452 if (IsWindows) {
1453 auto *Init = llvm::Function::Create(llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy,
1454 {}), llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage, ".block_isa_init",
1455 &CGM.getModule());
1456 llvm::IRBuilder<> b(llvm::BasicBlock::Create(CGM.getLLVMContext(), "entry",
1457 Init));
1458 b.CreateAlignedStore(CGM.getNSConcreteGlobalBlock(),
1459 b.CreateStructGEP(literal, 0), CGM.getPointerAlign().getQuantity());
1460 b.CreateRetVoid();
1461 // We can't use the normal LLVM global initialisation array, because we
1462 // need to specify that this runs early in library initialisation.
1463 auto *InitVar = new llvm::GlobalVariable(CGM.getModule(), Init->getType(),
1464 /*isConstant*/true, llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,
1465 Init, ".block_isa_init_ptr");
1466 InitVar->setSection(".CRT$XCLa");
1467 CGM.addUsedGlobal(InitVar);
1468 }
1469
1470 // Return a constant of the appropriately-casted type.
1471 llvm::Type *RequiredType =
1472 CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(blockInfo.getBlockExpr()->getType());
1473 llvm::Constant *Result =
1474 llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerCast(literal, RequiredType);
1475 CGM.setAddrOfGlobalBlock(blockInfo.BlockExpression, Result);
1476 if (CGM.getContext().getLangOpts().OpenCL)
1477 CGM.getOpenCLRuntime().recordBlockInfo(
1478 blockInfo.BlockExpression,
1479 cast<llvm::Function>(blockFn->stripPointerCasts()), Result);
1480 return Result;
1481}
1482
1483void CodeGenFunction::setBlockContextParameter(const ImplicitParamDecl *D,
1484 unsigned argNum,
1485 llvm::Value *arg) {
1486 assert(BlockInfo && "not emitting prologue of block invocation function?!");
1487
1488 // Allocate a stack slot like for any local variable to guarantee optimal
1489 // debug info at -O0. The mem2reg pass will eliminate it when optimizing.
1490 Address alloc = CreateMemTemp(D->getType(), D->getName() + ".addr");
1491 Builder.CreateStore(arg, alloc);
1492 if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getDebugInfo()) {
1493 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getDebugInfo() >=
1494 codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo) {
1495 DI->setLocation(D->getLocation());
1496 DI->EmitDeclareOfBlockLiteralArgVariable(
1497 *BlockInfo, D->getName(), argNum,
1498 cast<llvm::AllocaInst>(alloc.getPointer()), Builder);
1499 }
1500 }
1501
1502 SourceLocation StartLoc = BlockInfo->getBlockExpr()->getBody()->getBeginLoc();
1503 ApplyDebugLocation Scope(*this, StartLoc);
1504
1505 // Instead of messing around with LocalDeclMap, just set the value
1506 // directly as BlockPointer.
1507 BlockPointer = Builder.CreatePointerCast(
1508 arg,
1509 BlockInfo->StructureType->getPointerTo(
1510 getContext().getLangOpts().OpenCL
1511 ? CGM.getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_generic)
1512 : CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS()),
1513 "block");
1514}
1515
1516Address CodeGenFunction::LoadBlockStruct() {
1517 assert(BlockInfo && "not in a block invocation function!");
1518 assert(BlockPointer && "no block pointer set!");
1519 return Address(BlockPointer, BlockInfo->BlockAlign);
1520}
1521
1522llvm::Function *
1523CodeGenFunction::GenerateBlockFunction(GlobalDecl GD,
1524 const CGBlockInfo &blockInfo,
1525 const DeclMapTy &ldm,
1526 bool IsLambdaConversionToBlock,
1527 bool BuildGlobalBlock) {
1528 const BlockDecl *blockDecl = blockInfo.getBlockDecl();
1529
1530 CurGD = GD;
1531
1532 CurEHLocation = blockInfo.getBlockExpr()->getEndLoc();
1533
1534 BlockInfo = &blockInfo;
1535
1536 // Arrange for local static and local extern declarations to appear
1537 // to be local to this function as well, in case they're directly
1538 // referenced in a block.
1539 for (DeclMapTy::const_iterator i = ldm.begin(), e = ldm.end(); i != e; ++i) {
1540 const auto *var = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(i->first);
1541 if (var && !var->hasLocalStorage())
1542 setAddrOfLocalVar(var, i->second);
1543 }
1544
1545 // Begin building the function declaration.
1546
1547 // Build the argument list.
1548 FunctionArgList args;
1549
1550 // The first argument is the block pointer. Just take it as a void*
1551 // and cast it later.
1552 QualType selfTy = getContext().VoidPtrTy;
1553
1554 // For OpenCL passed block pointer can be private AS local variable or
1555 // global AS program scope variable (for the case with and without captures).
1556 // Generic AS is used therefore to be able to accommodate both private and
1557 // generic AS in one implementation.
1558 if (getLangOpts().OpenCL)
1559 selfTy = getContext().getPointerType(getContext().getAddrSpaceQualType(
1560 getContext().VoidTy, LangAS::opencl_generic));
1561
1562 IdentifierInfo *II = &CGM.getContext().Idents.get(".block_descriptor");
1563
1564 ImplicitParamDecl SelfDecl(getContext(), const_cast<BlockDecl *>(blockDecl),
1565 SourceLocation(), II, selfTy,
1566 ImplicitParamDecl::ObjCSelf);
1567 args.push_back(&SelfDecl);
1568
1569 // Now add the rest of the parameters.
1570 args.append(blockDecl->param_begin(), blockDecl->param_end());
1571
1572 // Create the function declaration.
1573 const FunctionProtoType *fnType = blockInfo.getBlockExpr()->getFunctionType();
1574 const CGFunctionInfo &fnInfo =
1575 CGM.getTypes().arrangeBlockFunctionDeclaration(fnType, args);
1576 if (CGM.ReturnSlotInterferesWithArgs(fnInfo))
1577 blockInfo.UsesStret = true;
1578
1579 llvm::FunctionType *fnLLVMType = CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(fnInfo);
1580
1581 StringRef name = CGM.getBlockMangledName(GD, blockDecl);
1582 llvm::Function *fn = llvm::Function::Create(
1583 fnLLVMType, llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage, name, &CGM.getModule());
1584 CGM.SetInternalFunctionAttributes(blockDecl, fn, fnInfo);
1585
1586 if (BuildGlobalBlock) {
1587 auto GenVoidPtrTy = getContext().getLangOpts().OpenCL
1588 ? CGM.getOpenCLRuntime().getGenericVoidPointerType()
1589 : VoidPtrTy;
1590 buildGlobalBlock(CGM, blockInfo,
1591 llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerCast(fn, GenVoidPtrTy));
1592 }
1593
1594 // Begin generating the function.
1595 StartFunction(blockDecl, fnType->getReturnType(), fn, fnInfo, args,
1596 blockDecl->getLocation(),
1597 blockInfo.getBlockExpr()->getBody()->getBeginLoc());
1598
1599 // Okay. Undo some of what StartFunction did.
1600
1601 // At -O0 we generate an explicit alloca for the BlockPointer, so the RA
1602 // won't delete the dbg.declare intrinsics for captured variables.
1603 llvm::Value *BlockPointerDbgLoc = BlockPointer;
1604 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel == 0) {
1605 // Allocate a stack slot for it, so we can point the debugger to it
1606 Address Alloca = CreateTempAlloca(BlockPointer->getType(),
1607 getPointerAlign(),
1608 "block.addr");
1609 // Set the DebugLocation to empty, so the store is recognized as a
1610 // frame setup instruction by llvm::DwarfDebug::beginFunction().
1611 auto NL = ApplyDebugLocation::CreateEmpty(*this);
1612 Builder.CreateStore(BlockPointer, Alloca);
1613 BlockPointerDbgLoc = Alloca.getPointer();
1614 }
1615
1616 // If we have a C++ 'this' reference, go ahead and force it into
1617 // existence now.
1618 if (blockDecl->capturesCXXThis()) {
1619 Address addr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(
1620 LoadBlockStruct(), blockInfo.CXXThisIndex, "block.captured-this");
1621 CXXThisValue = Builder.CreateLoad(addr, "this");
1622 }
1623
1624 // Also force all the constant captures.
1625 for (const auto &CI : blockDecl->captures()) {
1626 const VarDecl *variable = CI.getVariable();
1627 const CGBlockInfo::Capture &capture = blockInfo.getCapture(variable);
1628 if (!capture.isConstant()) continue;
1629
1630 CharUnits align = getContext().getDeclAlign(variable);
1631 Address alloca =
1632 CreateMemTemp(variable->getType(), align, "block.captured-const");
1633
1634 Builder.CreateStore(capture.getConstant(), alloca);
1635
1636 setAddrOfLocalVar(variable, alloca);
1637 }
1638
1639 // Save a spot to insert the debug information for all the DeclRefExprs.
1640 llvm::BasicBlock *entry = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
1641 llvm::BasicBlock::iterator entry_ptr = Builder.GetInsertPoint();
1642 --entry_ptr;
1643
1644 if (IsLambdaConversionToBlock)
1645 EmitLambdaBlockInvokeBody();
1646 else {
1647 PGO.assignRegionCounters(GlobalDecl(blockDecl), fn);
1648 incrementProfileCounter(blockDecl->getBody());
1649 EmitStmt(blockDecl->getBody());
1650 }
1651
1652 // Remember where we were...
1653 llvm::BasicBlock *resume = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
1654
1655 // Go back to the entry.
1656 ++entry_ptr;
1657 Builder.SetInsertPoint(entry, entry_ptr);
1658
1659 // Emit debug information for all the DeclRefExprs.
1660 // FIXME: also for 'this'
1661 if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getDebugInfo()) {
1662 for (const auto &CI : blockDecl->captures()) {
1663 const VarDecl *variable = CI.getVariable();
1664 DI->EmitLocation(Builder, variable->getLocation());
1665
1666 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getDebugInfo() >=
1667 codegenoptions::LimitedDebugInfo) {
1668 const CGBlockInfo::Capture &capture = blockInfo.getCapture(variable);
1669 if (capture.isConstant()) {
1670 auto addr = LocalDeclMap.find(variable)->second;
1671 (void)DI->EmitDeclareOfAutoVariable(variable, addr.getPointer(),
1672 Builder);
1673 continue;
1674 }
1675
1676 DI->EmitDeclareOfBlockDeclRefVariable(
1677 variable, BlockPointerDbgLoc, Builder, blockInfo,
1678 entry_ptr == entry->end() ? nullptr : &*entry_ptr);
1679 }
1680 }
1681 // Recover location if it was changed in the above loop.
1682 DI->EmitLocation(Builder,
1683 cast<CompoundStmt>(blockDecl->getBody())->getRBracLoc());
1684 }
1685
1686 // And resume where we left off.
1687 if (resume == nullptr)
1688 Builder.ClearInsertionPoint();
1689 else
1690 Builder.SetInsertPoint(resume);
1691
1692 FinishFunction(cast<CompoundStmt>(blockDecl->getBody())->getRBracLoc());
1693
1694 return fn;
1695}
1696
1697static std::pair<BlockCaptureEntityKind, BlockFieldFlags>
1698computeCopyInfoForBlockCapture(const BlockDecl::Capture &CI, QualType T,
1699 const LangOptions &LangOpts) {
1700 if (CI.getCopyExpr()) {
1701 assert(!CI.isByRef());
1702 // don't bother computing flags
1703 return std::make_pair(BlockCaptureEntityKind::CXXRecord, BlockFieldFlags());
1704 }
1705 BlockFieldFlags Flags;
1706 if (CI.isEscapingByref()) {
1707 Flags = BLOCK_FIELD_IS_BYREF;
1708 if (T.isObjCGCWeak())
1709 Flags |= BLOCK_FIELD_IS_WEAK;
1710 return std::make_pair(BlockCaptureEntityKind::BlockObject, Flags);
1711 }
1712
1713 Flags = BLOCK_FIELD_IS_OBJECT;
1714 bool isBlockPointer = T->isBlockPointerType();
1715 if (isBlockPointer)
1716 Flags = BLOCK_FIELD_IS_BLOCK;
1717
1718 switch (T.isNonTrivialToPrimitiveCopy()) {
1719 case QualType::PCK_Struct:
1720 return std::make_pair(BlockCaptureEntityKind::NonTrivialCStruct,
1721 BlockFieldFlags());
1722 case QualType::PCK_ARCWeak:
1723 // We need to register __weak direct captures with the runtime.
1724 return std::make_pair(BlockCaptureEntityKind::ARCWeak, Flags);
1725 case QualType::PCK_ARCStrong:
1726 // We need to retain the copied value for __strong direct captures.
1727 // If it's a block pointer, we have to copy the block and assign that to
1728 // the destination pointer, so we might as well use _Block_object_assign.
1729 // Otherwise we can avoid that.
1730 return std::make_pair(!isBlockPointer ? BlockCaptureEntityKind::ARCStrong
1731 : BlockCaptureEntityKind::BlockObject,
1732 Flags);
1733 case QualType::PCK_Trivial:
1734 case QualType::PCK_VolatileTrivial: {
1735 if (!T->isObjCRetainableType())
1736 // For all other types, the memcpy is fine.
1737 return std::make_pair(BlockCaptureEntityKind::None, BlockFieldFlags());
1738
1739 // Special rules for ARC captures:
1740 Qualifiers QS = T.getQualifiers();
1741
1742 // Non-ARC captures of retainable pointers are strong and
1743 // therefore require a call to _Block_object_assign.
1744 if (!QS.getObjCLifetime() && !LangOpts.ObjCAutoRefCount)
1745 return std::make_pair(BlockCaptureEntityKind::BlockObject, Flags);
1746
1747 // Otherwise the memcpy is fine.
1748 return std::make_pair(BlockCaptureEntityKind::None, BlockFieldFlags());
1749 }
1750 }
1751 llvm_unreachable("after exhaustive PrimitiveCopyKind switch");
1752}
1753
1754static std::pair<BlockCaptureEntityKind, BlockFieldFlags>
1755computeDestroyInfoForBlockCapture(const BlockDecl::Capture &CI, QualType T,
1756 const LangOptions &LangOpts);
1757
1758/// Find the set of block captures that need to be explicitly copied or destroy.
1759static void findBlockCapturedManagedEntities(
1760 const CGBlockInfo &BlockInfo, const LangOptions &LangOpts,
1761 SmallVectorImpl<BlockCaptureManagedEntity> &ManagedCaptures) {
1762 for (const auto &CI : BlockInfo.getBlockDecl()->captures()) {
1763 const VarDecl *Variable = CI.getVariable();
1764 const CGBlockInfo::Capture &Capture = BlockInfo.getCapture(Variable);
1765 if (Capture.isConstant())
1766 continue;
1767
1768 QualType VT = Capture.fieldType();
1769 auto CopyInfo = computeCopyInfoForBlockCapture(CI, VT, LangOpts);
1770 auto DisposeInfo = computeDestroyInfoForBlockCapture(CI, VT, LangOpts);
1771 if (CopyInfo.first != BlockCaptureEntityKind::None ||
1772 DisposeInfo.first != BlockCaptureEntityKind::None)
1773 ManagedCaptures.emplace_back(CopyInfo.first, DisposeInfo.first,
1774 CopyInfo.second, DisposeInfo.second, CI,
1775 Capture);
1776 }
1777
1778 // Sort the captures by offset.
1779 llvm::sort(ManagedCaptures);
1780}

1782namespace {
1783/// Release a __block variable.
1784struct CallBlockRelease final : EHScopeStack::Cleanup {
1785 Address Addr;
1786 BlockFieldFlags FieldFlags;
1787 bool LoadBlockVarAddr, CanThrow;
1788
1789 CallBlockRelease(Address Addr, BlockFieldFlags Flags, bool LoadValue,
1790 bool CT)
1791 : Addr(Addr), FieldFlags(Flags), LoadBlockVarAddr(LoadValue),
1792 CanThrow(CT) {}
1793
1794 void Emit(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Flags flags) override {
1795 llvm::Value *BlockVarAddr;
1796 if (LoadBlockVarAddr) {
1797 BlockVarAddr = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Addr);
1798 BlockVarAddr = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(BlockVarAddr, CGF.VoidPtrTy);
1799 } else {
1800 BlockVarAddr = Addr.getPointer();
1801 }
1802
1803 CGF.BuildBlockRelease(BlockVarAddr, FieldFlags, CanThrow);
1804 }
1805};
1806} // end anonymous namespace

1808/// Check if \p T is a C++ class that has a destructor that can throw.
1809bool CodeGenFunction::cxxDestructorCanThrow(QualType T) {
1810 if (const auto *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
1811 if (const CXXDestructorDecl *DD = RD->getDestructor())
1812 return DD->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>()->canThrow();
1813 return false;
1814}
1815
1816// Return a string that has the information about a capture.
1817static std::string getBlockCaptureStr(const BlockCaptureManagedEntity &E,
1818 CaptureStrKind StrKind,
1819 CharUnits BlockAlignment,
1820 CodeGenModule &CGM) {
1821 std::string Str;
1822 ASTContext &Ctx = CGM.getContext();
1823 const BlockDecl::Capture &CI = *E.CI;
1824 QualType CaptureTy = CI.getVariable()->getType();
1825
1826 BlockCaptureEntityKind Kind;
1827 BlockFieldFlags Flags;
1828
1829 // CaptureStrKind::Merged should be passed only when the operations and the
1830 // flags are the same for copy and dispose.
1831 assert((StrKind != CaptureStrKind::Merged ||
1832 (E.CopyKind == E.DisposeKind && E.CopyFlags == E.DisposeFlags)) &&
1833 "different operations and flags");
1834
1835 if (StrKind == CaptureStrKind::DisposeHelper) {
1836 Kind = E.DisposeKind;
1837 Flags = E.DisposeFlags;
1838 } else {
1839 Kind = E.CopyKind;
1840 Flags = E.CopyFlags;
1841 }
1842
1843 switch (Kind) {
1844 case BlockCaptureEntityKind::CXXRecord: {
1845 Str += "c";
1846 SmallString<256> TyStr;
1847 llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(TyStr);
1848 CGM.getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleTypeName(CaptureTy, Out);
1849 Str += llvm::to_string(TyStr.size()) + TyStr.c_str();
1850 break;
1851 }
1852 case BlockCaptureEntityKind::ARCWeak:
1853 Str += "w";
1854 break;
1855 case BlockCaptureEntityKind::ARCStrong:
1856 Str += "s";
1857 break;
1858 case BlockCaptureEntityKind::BlockObject: {
1859 const VarDecl *Var = CI.getVariable();
1860 unsigned F = Flags.getBitMask();
1861 if (F & BLOCK_FIELD_IS_BYREF) {
1862 Str += "r";
1863 if (F & BLOCK_FIELD_IS_WEAK)
1864 Str += "w";
1865 else {
1866 // If CaptureStrKind::Merged is passed, check both the copy expression
1867 // and the destructor.
1868 if (StrKind != CaptureStrKind::DisposeHelper) {
1869 if (Ctx.getBlockVarCopyInit(Var).canThrow())
1870 Str += "c";
1871 }
1872 if (StrKind != CaptureStrKind::CopyHelper) {
1873 if (CodeGenFunction::cxxDestructorCanThrow(CaptureTy))
1874 Str += "d";
1875 }
1876 }
1877 } else {
1878 assert((F & BLOCK_FIELD_IS_OBJECT) && "unexpected flag value");
1879 if (F == BLOCK_FIELD_IS_BLOCK)
1880 Str += "b";
1881 else
1882 Str += "o";
1883 }
1884 break;
1885 }
1886 case BlockCaptureEntityKind::NonTrivialCStruct: {
1887 bool IsVolatile = CaptureTy.isVolatileQualified();
1888 CharUnits Alignment =
1889 BlockAlignment.alignmentAtOffset(E.Capture->getOffset());
1890
1891 Str += "n";
1892 std::string FuncStr;
1893 if (StrKind == CaptureStrKind::DisposeHelper)
1894 FuncStr = CodeGenFunction::getNonTrivialDestructorStr(
1895 CaptureTy, Alignment, IsVolatile, Ctx);
1896 else
1897 // If CaptureStrKind::Merged is passed, use the copy constructor string.
1898 // It has all the information that the destructor string has.
1899 FuncStr = CodeGenFunction::getNonTrivialCopyConstructorStr(
1900 CaptureTy, Alignment, IsVolatile, Ctx);
1901 // The underscore is necessary here because non-trivial copy constructor
1902 // and destructor strings can start with a number.
1903 Str += llvm::to_string(FuncStr.size()) + "_" + FuncStr;
1904 break;
1905 }
1906 case BlockCaptureEntityKind::None:
1907 break;
1908 }
1909
1910 return Str;
1911}
1912
1913static std::string getCopyDestroyHelperFuncName(
1914 const SmallVectorImpl<BlockCaptureManagedEntity> &Captures,
1915 CharUnits BlockAlignment, CaptureStrKind StrKind, CodeGenModule &CGM) {
1916 assert((StrKind == CaptureStrKind::CopyHelper ||
1917 StrKind == CaptureStrKind::DisposeHelper) &&
1918 "unexpected CaptureStrKind");
1919 std::string Name = StrKind == CaptureStrKind::CopyHelper
1920 ? "__copy_helper_block_"
1921 : "__destroy_helper_block_";
1922 if (CGM.getLangOpts().Exceptions)
1923 Name += "e";
1924 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().ObjCAutoRefCountExceptions)
1925 Name += "a";
1926 Name += llvm::to_string(BlockAlignment.getQuantity()) + "_";
1927
1928 for (const BlockCaptureManagedEntity &E : Captures) {
1929 Name += llvm::to_string(E.Capture->getOffset().getQuantity());
1930 Name += getBlockCaptureStr(E, StrKind, BlockAlignment, CGM);
1931 }
1932
1933 return Name;
1934}
1935
1936static void pushCaptureCleanup(BlockCaptureEntityKind CaptureKind,
1937 Address Field, QualType CaptureType,
1938 BlockFieldFlags Flags, bool ForCopyHelper,
1939 VarDecl *Var, CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
1940 bool EHOnly = ForCopyHelper;
1941
1942 switch (CaptureKind) {
1943 case BlockCaptureEntityKind::CXXRecord:
1944 case BlockCaptureEntityKind::ARCWeak:
1945 case BlockCaptureEntityKind::NonTrivialCStruct:
1946 case BlockCaptureEntityKind::ARCStrong: {
1947 if (CaptureType.isDestructedType() &&
1948 (!EHOnly || CGF.needsEHCleanup(CaptureType.isDestructedType()))) {
1949 CodeGenFunction::Destroyer *Destroyer =
1950 CaptureKind == BlockCaptureEntityKind::ARCStrong
1951 ? CodeGenFunction::destroyARCStrongImprecise
1952 : CGF.getDestroyer(CaptureType.isDestructedType());
1953 CleanupKind Kind =
1954 EHOnly ? EHCleanup
1955 : CGF.getCleanupKind(CaptureType.isDestructedType());
1956 CGF.pushDestroy(Kind, Field, CaptureType, Destroyer, Kind & EHCleanup);
1957 }
1958 break;
1959 }
1960 case BlockCaptureEntityKind::BlockObject: {
1961 if (!EHOnly || CGF.getLangOpts().Exceptions) {
1962 CleanupKind Kind = EHOnly ? EHCleanup : NormalAndEHCleanup;
1963 // Calls to _Block_object_dispose along the EH path in the copy helper
1964 // function don't throw as newly-copied __block variables always have a
1965 // reference count of 2.
1966 bool CanThrow =
1967 !ForCopyHelper && CGF.cxxDestructorCanThrow(CaptureType);
1968 CGF.enterByrefCleanup(Kind, Field, Flags, /*LoadBlockVarAddr*/ true,
1969 CanThrow);
1970 }
1971 break;
1972 }
1973 case BlockCaptureEntityKind::None:
1974 break;
1975 }
1976}

1978static void setBlockHelperAttributesVisibility(bool CapturesNonExternalType,
1979 llvm::Function *Fn,
1980 const CGFunctionInfo &FI,
1981 CodeGenModule &CGM) {
1982 if (CapturesNonExternalType) {
1983 CGM.SetInternalFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl(), Fn, FI);
1984 } else {
1985 Fn->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
1986 Fn->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
1987 CGM.SetLLVMFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl(), FI, Fn);
1988 CGM.SetLLVMFunctionAttributesForDefinition(nullptr, Fn);
1989 }
