1991/// Generate the copy-helper function for a block closure object:
1992/// static void block_copy_helper(block_t *dst, block_t *src);
1993/// The runtime will have previously initialized 'dst' by doing a
1994/// bit-copy of 'src'.
1995///
1996/// Note that this copies an entire block closure object to the heap;
1997/// it should not be confused with a 'byref copy helper', which moves
1998/// the contents of an individual __block variable to the heap.
1999llvm::Constant *
2000CodeGenFunction::GenerateCopyHelperFunction(const CGBlockInfo &blockInfo) {
2001 SmallVector<BlockCaptureManagedEntity, 4> CopiedCaptures;
2002 findBlockCapturedManagedEntities(blockInfo, getLangOpts(), CopiedCaptures);
2003 std::string FuncName =
2004 getCopyDestroyHelperFuncName(CopiedCaptures, blockInfo.BlockAlign,
2005 CaptureStrKind::CopyHelper, CGM);
2006
2007 if (llvm::GlobalValue *Func = CGM.getModule().getNamedValue(FuncName))
2008 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(Func, VoidPtrTy);
2009
2010 ASTContext &C = getContext();
2011
2012 QualType ReturnTy = C.VoidTy;
2013
2014 FunctionArgList args;
2015 ImplicitParamDecl DstDecl(C, C.VoidPtrTy, ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
2016 args.push_back(&DstDecl);
2017 ImplicitParamDecl SrcDecl(C, C.VoidPtrTy, ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
2018 args.push_back(&SrcDecl);
2019
2020 const CGFunctionInfo &FI =
2021 CGM.getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(ReturnTy, args);
2022
2023 // FIXME: it would be nice if these were mergeable with things with
2024 // identical semantics.
2025 llvm::FunctionType *LTy = CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(FI);
2026
2027 llvm::Function *Fn =
2028 llvm::Function::Create(LTy, llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage,
2029 FuncName, &CGM.getModule());
2030 if (CGM.supportsCOMDAT())
2031 Fn->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(FuncName));
2032
2033 IdentifierInfo *II = &C.Idents.get(FuncName);
2034
2035 SmallVector<QualType, 2> ArgTys;
2036 ArgTys.push_back(C.VoidPtrTy);
2037 ArgTys.push_back(C.VoidPtrTy);
2038 QualType FunctionTy = C.getFunctionType(ReturnTy, ArgTys, {});
2039
2040 FunctionDecl *FD = FunctionDecl::Create(
2041 C, C.getTranslationUnitDecl(), SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(), II,
2042 FunctionTy, nullptr, SC_Static, false, false);
2043
2044 setBlockHelperAttributesVisibility(blockInfo.CapturesNonExternalType, Fn, FI,
2045 CGM);
2046 StartFunction(FD, ReturnTy, Fn, FI, args);
2047 ApplyDebugLocation NL{*this, blockInfo.getBlockExpr()->getBeginLoc()};
2048 const auto DefaultAS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
2049 llvm::Type *structPtrTy = blockInfo.StructureType->getPointerTo(DefaultAS);
2050
2051 Address src = GetAddrOfLocalVar(&SrcDecl);
2052 src = Address(Builder.CreateLoad(src), blockInfo.BlockAlign);
2053 src = Builder.CreateBitCast(src, structPtrTy, "block.source");
2054
2055 Address dst = GetAddrOfLocalVar(&DstDecl);
2056 dst = Address(Builder.CreateLoad(dst), blockInfo.BlockAlign);
2057 dst = Builder.CreateBitCast(dst, structPtrTy, "block.dest");
2058
2059 for (const auto &CopiedCapture : CopiedCaptures) {
2060 const BlockDecl::Capture &CI = *CopiedCapture.CI;
2061 const CGBlockInfo::Capture &capture = *CopiedCapture.Capture;
2062 QualType captureType = CI.getVariable()->getType();
2063 BlockFieldFlags flags = CopiedCapture.CopyFlags;
2064
2065 unsigned index = capture.getIndex();
2066 Address srcField = Builder.CreateStructGEP(src, index);
2067 Address dstField = Builder.CreateStructGEP(dst, index);
2068
2069 switch (CopiedCapture.CopyKind) {
2070 case BlockCaptureEntityKind::CXXRecord:
2071 // If there's an explicit copy expression, we do that.
2072 assert(CI.getCopyExpr() && "copy expression for variable is missing");
2073 EmitSynthesizedCXXCopyCtor(dstField, srcField, CI.getCopyExpr());
2074 break;
2075 case BlockCaptureEntityKind::ARCWeak:
2076 EmitARCCopyWeak(dstField, srcField);
2077 break;
2078 case BlockCaptureEntityKind::NonTrivialCStruct: {
2079 // If this is a C struct that requires non-trivial copy construction,
2080 // emit a call to its copy constructor.
2081 QualType varType = CI.getVariable()->getType();
2082 callCStructCopyConstructor(MakeAddrLValue(dstField, varType),
2083 MakeAddrLValue(srcField, varType));
2084 break;
2085 }
2086 case BlockCaptureEntityKind::ARCStrong: {
2087 llvm::Value *srcValue = Builder.CreateLoad(srcField, "blockcopy.src");
2088 // At -O0, store null into the destination field (so that the
2089 // storeStrong doesn't over-release) and then call storeStrong.
2090 // This is a workaround to not having an initStrong call.
2091 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel == 0) {
2092 auto *ty = cast<llvm::PointerType>(srcValue->getType());
2093 llvm::Value *null = llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(ty);
2094 Builder.CreateStore(null, dstField);
2095 EmitARCStoreStrongCall(dstField, srcValue, true);
2096
2097 // With optimization enabled, take advantage of the fact that
2098 // the blocks runtime guarantees a memcpy of the block data, and
2099 // just emit a retain of the src field.
2100 } else {
2101 EmitARCRetainNonBlock(srcValue);
2102
2103 // Unless EH cleanup is required, we don't need this anymore, so kill
2104 // it. It's not quite worth the annoyance to avoid creating it in the
2105 // first place.
2106 if (!needsEHCleanup(captureType.isDestructedType()))
2107 cast<llvm::Instruction>(dstField.getPointer())->eraseFromParent();
2108 }
2109 break;
2110 }
2111 case BlockCaptureEntityKind::BlockObject: {
2112 llvm::Value *srcValue = Builder.CreateLoad(srcField, "blockcopy.src");
2113 srcValue = Builder.CreateBitCast(srcValue, VoidPtrTy);
2114 llvm::Value *dstAddr =
2115 Builder.CreateBitCast(dstField.getPointer(), VoidPtrTy);
2116 llvm::Value *args[] = {
2117 dstAddr, srcValue, llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, flags.getBitMask())
2118 };
2119
2120 if (CI.isByRef() && C.getBlockVarCopyInit(CI.getVariable()).canThrow())
2121 EmitRuntimeCallOrInvoke(CGM.getBlockObjectAssign(), args);
2122 else
2123 EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(CGM.getBlockObjectAssign(), args);
2124 break;
2125 }
2126 case BlockCaptureEntityKind::None:
2127 continue;
2128 }
2129
2130 // Ensure that we destroy the copied object if an exception is thrown later
2131 // in the helper function.
2132 pushCaptureCleanup(CopiedCapture.CopyKind, dstField, captureType, flags,
2133 /*ForCopyHelper*/ true, CI.getVariable(), *this);
2134 }
2135
2136 FinishFunction();
2137
2138 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(Fn, VoidPtrTy);
2139}
2140
2141static BlockFieldFlags
2142getBlockFieldFlagsForObjCObjectPointer(const BlockDecl::Capture &CI,
2143 QualType T) {
2144 BlockFieldFlags Flags = BLOCK_FIELD_IS_OBJECT;
2145 if (T->isBlockPointerType())
2146 Flags = BLOCK_FIELD_IS_BLOCK;
2147 return Flags;
2148}
2149
2150static std::pair<BlockCaptureEntityKind, BlockFieldFlags>
2151computeDestroyInfoForBlockCapture(const BlockDecl::Capture &CI, QualType T,
2152 const LangOptions &LangOpts) {
2153 if (CI.isEscapingByref()) {
2154 BlockFieldFlags Flags = BLOCK_FIELD_IS_BYREF;
2155 if (T.isObjCGCWeak())
2156 Flags |= BLOCK_FIELD_IS_WEAK;
2157 return std::make_pair(BlockCaptureEntityKind::BlockObject, Flags);
2158 }
2159
2160 switch (T.isDestructedType()) {
2161 case QualType::DK_cxx_destructor:
2162 return std::make_pair(BlockCaptureEntityKind::CXXRecord, BlockFieldFlags());
2163 case QualType::DK_objc_strong_lifetime:
2164 // Use objc_storeStrong for __strong direct captures; the
2165 // dynamic tools really like it when we do this.
2166 return std::make_pair(BlockCaptureEntityKind::ARCStrong,
2167 getBlockFieldFlagsForObjCObjectPointer(CI, T));
2168 case QualType::DK_objc_weak_lifetime:
2169 // Support __weak direct captures.
2170 return std::make_pair(BlockCaptureEntityKind::ARCWeak,
2171 getBlockFieldFlagsForObjCObjectPointer(CI, T));
2172 case QualType::DK_nontrivial_c_struct:
2173 return std::make_pair(BlockCaptureEntityKind::NonTrivialCStruct,
2174 BlockFieldFlags());
2175 case QualType::DK_none: {
2176 // Non-ARC captures are strong, and we need to use _Block_object_dispose.
2177 if (T->isObjCRetainableType() && !T.getQualifiers().hasObjCLifetime() &&
2178 !LangOpts.ObjCAutoRefCount)
2179 return std::make_pair(BlockCaptureEntityKind::BlockObject,
2180 getBlockFieldFlagsForObjCObjectPointer(CI, T));
2181 // Otherwise, we have nothing to do.
2182 return std::make_pair(BlockCaptureEntityKind::None, BlockFieldFlags());
2183 }
2184 }
2185 llvm_unreachable("after exhaustive DestructionKind switch");
2186}

2188/// Generate the destroy-helper function for a block closure object:
2189/// static void block_destroy_helper(block_t *theBlock);
2190///
2191/// Note that this destroys a heap-allocated block closure object;
2192/// it should not be confused with a 'byref destroy helper', which
2193/// destroys the heap-allocated contents of an individual __block
2194/// variable.
2195llvm::Constant *
2196CodeGenFunction::GenerateDestroyHelperFunction(const CGBlockInfo &blockInfo) {
2197 SmallVector<BlockCaptureManagedEntity, 4> DestroyedCaptures;
2198 findBlockCapturedManagedEntities(blockInfo, getLangOpts(), DestroyedCaptures);
2199 std::string FuncName =
2200 getCopyDestroyHelperFuncName(DestroyedCaptures, blockInfo.BlockAlign,
2201 CaptureStrKind::DisposeHelper, CGM);
2202
2203 if (llvm::GlobalValue *Func = CGM.getModule().getNamedValue(FuncName))
2204 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(Func, VoidPtrTy);
2205
2206 ASTContext &C = getContext();
2207
2208 QualType ReturnTy = C.VoidTy;
2209
2210 FunctionArgList args;
2211 ImplicitParamDecl SrcDecl(C, C.VoidPtrTy, ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
2212 args.push_back(&SrcDecl);
2213
2214 const CGFunctionInfo &FI =
2215 CGM.getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(ReturnTy, args);
2216
2217 // FIXME: We'd like to put these into a mergable by content, with
2218 // internal linkage.
2219 llvm::FunctionType *LTy = CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(FI);
2220
2221 llvm::Function *Fn =
2222 llvm::Function::Create(LTy, llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage,
2223 FuncName, &CGM.getModule());
2224 if (CGM.supportsCOMDAT())
2225 Fn->setComdat(CGM.getModule().getOrInsertComdat(FuncName));
2226
2227 IdentifierInfo *II = &C.Idents.get(FuncName);
2228
2229 SmallVector<QualType, 1> ArgTys;
2230 ArgTys.push_back(C.VoidPtrTy);
2231 QualType FunctionTy = C.getFunctionType(ReturnTy, ArgTys, {});
2232
2233 FunctionDecl *FD = FunctionDecl::Create(
2234 C, C.getTranslationUnitDecl(), SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(), II,
2235 FunctionTy, nullptr, SC_Static, false, false);
2236
2237 setBlockHelperAttributesVisibility(blockInfo.CapturesNonExternalType, Fn, FI,
2238 CGM);
2239 StartFunction(FD, ReturnTy, Fn, FI, args);
2240 markAsIgnoreThreadCheckingAtRuntime(Fn);
2241
2242 ApplyDebugLocation NL{*this, blockInfo.getBlockExpr()->getBeginLoc()};
2243
2244 llvm::Type *structPtrTy =
2245 blockInfo.StructureType->getPointerTo(
2246 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS());
2247
2248 Address src = GetAddrOfLocalVar(&SrcDecl);
2249 src = Address(Builder.CreateLoad(src), blockInfo.BlockAlign);
2250 src = Builder.CreateBitCast(src, structPtrTy, "block");
2251
2252 CodeGenFunction::RunCleanupsScope cleanups(*this);
2253
2254 for (const auto &DestroyedCapture : DestroyedCaptures) {
2255 const BlockDecl::Capture &CI = *DestroyedCapture.CI;
2256 const CGBlockInfo::Capture &capture = *DestroyedCapture.Capture;
2257 BlockFieldFlags flags = DestroyedCapture.DisposeFlags;
2258
2259 Address srcField = Builder.CreateStructGEP(src, capture.getIndex());
2260
2261 pushCaptureCleanup(DestroyedCapture.DisposeKind, srcField,
2262 CI.getVariable()->getType(), flags,
2263 /*ForCopyHelper*/ false, CI.getVariable(), *this);
2264 }
2265
2266 cleanups.ForceCleanup();
2267
2268 FinishFunction();
2269
2270 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(Fn, VoidPtrTy);
2271}

2455static llvm::Constant *
2456generateByrefCopyHelper(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const BlockByrefInfo &byrefInfo,
2457 BlockByrefHelpers &generator) {
2458 ASTContext &Context = CGF.getContext();
2459
2460 QualType ReturnTy = Context.VoidTy;
2461
2462 FunctionArgList args;
2463 ImplicitParamDecl Dst(Context, Context.VoidPtrTy, ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
2464 args.push_back(&Dst);
2465
2466 ImplicitParamDecl Src(Context, Context.VoidPtrTy, ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
2467 args.push_back(&Src);
2468
2469 const CGFunctionInfo &FI =
2470 CGF.CGM.getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(ReturnTy, args);
2471
2472 llvm::FunctionType *LTy = CGF.CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(FI);
2473
2474 // FIXME: We'd like to put these into a mergable by content, with
2475 // internal linkage.
2476 llvm::Function *Fn =
2477 llvm::Function::Create(LTy, llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,
2478 "__Block_byref_object_copy_", &CGF.CGM.getModule());
2479
2480 IdentifierInfo *II
2481 = &Context.Idents.get("__Block_byref_object_copy_");
2482
2483 SmallVector<QualType, 2> ArgTys;
2484 ArgTys.push_back(Context.VoidPtrTy);
2485 ArgTys.push_back(Context.VoidPtrTy);
2486 QualType FunctionTy = Context.getFunctionType(ReturnTy, ArgTys, {});
2487
2488 FunctionDecl *FD = FunctionDecl::Create(
2489 Context, Context.getTranslationUnitDecl(), SourceLocation(),
2490 SourceLocation(), II, FunctionTy, nullptr, SC_Static, false, false);
2491
2492 CGF.CGM.SetInternalFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl(), Fn, FI);
2493
2494 CGF.StartFunction(FD, ReturnTy, Fn, FI, args);
2495
2496 if (generator.needsCopy()) {
2497 llvm::Type *byrefPtrType =
2498 byrefInfo.Type->getPointerTo(
2499 CGF.CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS());
2500
2501 // dst->x
2502 Address destField = CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&Dst);
2503 destField = Address(CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(destField),
2504 byrefInfo.ByrefAlignment);
2505 destField = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(destField, byrefPtrType);
2506 destField = CGF.emitBlockByrefAddress(destField, byrefInfo, false,
2507 "dest-object");
2508
2509 // src->x
2510 Address srcField = CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&Src);
2511 srcField = Address(CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(srcField),
2512 byrefInfo.ByrefAlignment);
2513 srcField = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(srcField, byrefPtrType);
2514 srcField = CGF.emitBlockByrefAddress(srcField, byrefInfo, false,
2515 "src-object");
2516
2517 generator.emitCopy(CGF, destField, srcField);
2518 }
2519
2520 CGF.FinishFunction();
2521
2522 return llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(Fn, CGF.Int8PtrTy);
2523}

2533/// Generate code for a __block variable's dispose helper.
2534static llvm::Constant *
2535generateByrefDisposeHelper(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2536 const BlockByrefInfo &byrefInfo,
2537 BlockByrefHelpers &generator) {
2538 ASTContext &Context = CGF.getContext();
2539 QualType R = Context.VoidTy;
2540
2541 FunctionArgList args;
2542 ImplicitParamDecl Src(CGF.getContext(), Context.VoidPtrTy,
2543 ImplicitParamDecl::Other);
2544 args.push_back(&Src);
2545
2546 const CGFunctionInfo &FI =
2547 CGF.CGM.getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(R, args);
2548
2549 llvm::FunctionType *LTy = CGF.CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(FI);
2550
2551 // FIXME: We'd like to put these into a mergable by content, with
2552 // internal linkage.
2553 llvm::Function *Fn =
2554 llvm::Function::Create(LTy, llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,
2555 "__Block_byref_object_dispose_",
2556 &CGF.CGM.getModule());

2558 IdentifierInfo *II
2559 = &Context.Idents.get("__Block_byref_object_dispose_");
2560
2561 SmallVector<QualType, 1> ArgTys;
2562 ArgTys.push_back(Context.VoidPtrTy);
2563 QualType FunctionTy = Context.getFunctionType(R, ArgTys, {});
2564
2565 FunctionDecl *FD = FunctionDecl::Create(
2566 Context, Context.getTranslationUnitDecl(), SourceLocation(),
2567 SourceLocation(), II, FunctionTy, nullptr, SC_Static, false, false);
2568

2597/// Lazily build the copy and dispose helpers for a __block variable
2598/// with the given information.
2599template <class T>
2600static T *buildByrefHelpers(CodeGenModule &CGM, const BlockByrefInfo &byrefInfo,
2601 T &&generator) {
2602 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID id;
2603 generator.Profile(id);
2604
2605 void *insertPos;
2606 BlockByrefHelpers *node
2607 = CGM.ByrefHelpersCache.FindNodeOrInsertPos(id, insertPos);
2608 if (node) return static_cast<T*>(node);
2609
2610 generator.CopyHelper = buildByrefCopyHelper(CGM, byrefInfo, generator);
2611 generator.DisposeHelper = buildByrefDisposeHelper(CGM, byrefInfo, generator);
2612
2613 T *copy = new (CGM.getContext()) T(std::forward<T>(generator));
2614 CGM.ByrefHelpersCache.InsertNode(copy, insertPos);
2615 return copy;
2616}

2618/// Build the copy and dispose helpers for the given __block variable
2619/// emission. Places the helpers in the global cache. Returns null
2620/// if no helpers are required.
2621BlockByrefHelpers *
2622CodeGenFunction::buildByrefHelpers(llvm::StructType &byrefType,
2623 const AutoVarEmission &emission) {
2624 const VarDecl &var = *emission.Variable;
2625 assert(var.isEscapingByref() &&
2626 "only escaping __block variables need byref helpers");
2627
2628 QualType type = var.getType();
2629
2630 auto &byrefInfo = getBlockByrefInfo(&var);
2631
2632 // The alignment we care about for the purposes of uniquing byref
2633 // helpers is the alignment of the actual byref value field.
2634 CharUnits valueAlignment =
2635 byrefInfo.ByrefAlignment.alignmentAtOffset(byrefInfo.FieldOffset);
2636
2637 if (const CXXRecordDecl *record = type->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
2638 const Expr *copyExpr =
2639 CGM.getContext().getBlockVarCopyInit(&var).getCopyExpr();
2640 if (!copyExpr && record->hasTrivialDestructor()) return nullptr;
2641
2642 return ::buildByrefHelpers(
2643 CGM, byrefInfo, CXXByrefHelpers(valueAlignment, type, copyExpr));
2644 }
2645
2646 // If type is a non-trivial C struct type that is non-trivial to
2647 // destructly move or destroy, build the copy and dispose helpers.
2648 if (type.isNonTrivialToPrimitiveDestructiveMove() == QualType::PCK_Struct ||
2649 type.isDestructedType() == QualType::DK_nontrivial_c_struct)
2650 return ::buildByrefHelpers(
2651 CGM, byrefInfo, NonTrivialCStructByrefHelpers(valueAlignment, type));
2652
2653 // Otherwise, if we don't have a retainable type, there's nothing to do.
2654 // that the runtime does extra copies.
2655 if (!type->isObjCRetainableType()) return nullptr;
2656
2657 Qualifiers qs = type.getQualifiers();
2658
2659 // If we have lifetime, that dominates.
2660 if (Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime lifetime = qs.getObjCLifetime()) {
2661 switch (lifetime) {
2662 case Qualifiers::OCL_None: llvm_unreachable("impossible");
2663
2664 // These are just bits as far as the runtime is concerned.
2665 case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
2666 case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
2667 return nullptr;
2668
2669 // Tell the runtime that this is ARC __weak, called by the
2670 // byref routines.
2671 case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
2672 return ::buildByrefHelpers(CGM, byrefInfo,
2673 ARCWeakByrefHelpers(valueAlignment));
2674
2675 // ARC __strong __block variables need to be retained.
2676 case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
2677 // Block pointers need to be copied, and there's no direct
2678 // transfer possible.
2679 if (type->isBlockPointerType()) {
2680 return ::buildByrefHelpers(CGM, byrefInfo,
2681 ARCStrongBlockByrefHelpers(valueAlignment));
2682
2683 // Otherwise, we transfer ownership of the retain from the stack
2684 // to the heap.
2685 } else {
2686 return ::buildByrefHelpers(CGM, byrefInfo,
2687 ARCStrongByrefHelpers(valueAlignment));
2688 }
2689 }
2690 llvm_unreachable("fell out of lifetime switch!");
2691 }
2692
2693 BlockFieldFlags flags;
2694 if (type->isBlockPointerType()) {
2695 flags |= BLOCK_FIELD_IS_BLOCK;
2696 } else if (CGM.getContext().isObjCNSObjectType(type) ||
2697 type->isObjCObjectPointerType()) {
2698 flags |= BLOCK_FIELD_IS_OBJECT;
2699 } else {
2700 return nullptr;
2701 }
2702
2703 if (type.isObjCGCWeak())
2704 flags |= BLOCK_FIELD_IS_WEAK;
2705
2706 return ::buildByrefHelpers(CGM, byrefInfo,
2707 ObjectByrefHelpers(valueAlignment, flags));
2708}

2710Address CodeGenFunction::emitBlockByrefAddress(Address baseAddr,
2711 const VarDecl *var,
2712 bool followForward) {
2713 auto &info = getBlockByrefInfo(var);
2714 return emitBlockByrefAddress(baseAddr, info, followForward, var->getName());
2715}

2717Address CodeGenFunction::emitBlockByrefAddress(Address baseAddr,
2718 const BlockByrefInfo &info,
2719 bool followForward,
2720 const llvm::Twine &name) {
2721 // Chase the forwarding address if requested.
2722 if (followForward) {
2723 Address forwardingAddr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(baseAddr, 1, "forwarding");
2724 baseAddr = Address(Builder.CreateLoad(forwardingAddr), info.ByrefAlignment);
2725 }
2726
2727 return Builder.CreateStructGEP(baseAddr, info.FieldIndex, name);
2728}

2730/// BuildByrefInfo - This routine changes a __block variable declared as T x
2731/// into:
2732///
2733/// struct {
2734/// void *__isa;
2735/// void *__forwarding;
2736/// int32_t __flags;
2737/// int32_t __size;
2738/// void *__copy_helper; // only if needed
2739/// void *__destroy_helper; // only if needed
2740/// void *__byref_variable_layout;// only if needed
2741/// char padding[X]; // only if needed
2742/// T x;
2743/// } x
2744///
2745const BlockByrefInfo &CodeGenFunction::getBlockByrefInfo(const VarDecl *D) {
2746 auto it = BlockByrefInfos.find(D);
2747 if (it != BlockByrefInfos.end())
2748 return it->second;
2749
2750 llvm::StructType *byrefType =
2751 llvm::StructType::create(getLLVMContext(),
2752 "struct.__block_byref_" + D->getNameAsString());
2753
2754 QualType Ty = D->getType();
2755
2756 CharUnits size;
2757 SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 8> types;
2758
2759 // void *__isa;
2760 types.push_back(Int8PtrTy);
2761 size += getPointerSize();
2762
2763 // void *__forwarding;
2764 types.push_back(llvm::PointerType::get(byrefType,
2765 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS()));
2766 size += getPointerSize();
2767
2768 // int32_t __flags;
2769 types.push_back(Int32Ty);
2770 size += CharUnits::fromQuantity(4);
2771
2772 // int32_t __size;
2773 types.push_back(Int32Ty);
2774 size += CharUnits::fromQuantity(4);
2775 // If the pointer size is over 64 bits, there is padding after these.
2776 size = size.alignTo(getPointerAlign());
2777
2778 // Note that this must match *exactly* the logic in buildByrefHelpers.
2779 bool hasCopyAndDispose = getContext().BlockRequiresCopying(Ty, D);
2780 if (hasCopyAndDispose) {
2781 /// void *__copy_helper;
2782 types.push_back(Int8PtrTy);
2783 size += getPointerSize();
2784
2785 /// void *__destroy_helper;
2786 types.push_back(Int8PtrTy);
2787 size += getPointerSize();
2788 }
2789
2790 bool HasByrefExtendedLayout = false;
2791 Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime Lifetime;
2792 if (getContext().getByrefLifetime(Ty, Lifetime, HasByrefExtendedLayout) &&
2793 HasByrefExtendedLayout) {
2794 /// void *__byref_variable_layout;
2795 types.push_back(Int8PtrTy);
2796 size += CharUnits::fromQuantity(PointerSizeInBytes);
2797 }
2798
2799 // T x;
2800 llvm::Type *varTy = ConvertTypeForMem(Ty);
2801
2802 bool packed = false;
2803 CharUnits varAlign = getContext().getDeclAlign(D);
2804 CharUnits varOffset = size.alignTo(varAlign);
2805
2806 // We may have to insert padding.
2807 if (varOffset != size) {
2808 llvm::Type *paddingTy =
2809 llvm::ArrayType::get(Int8Ty, (varOffset - size).getQuantity());
2810
2811 types.push_back(paddingTy);
2812 size = varOffset;
2813
2814 // Conversely, we might have to prevent LLVM from inserting padding.
2815 } else if (CGM.getDataLayout().getABITypeAlignment(varTy)
2816 > varAlign.getQuantity()) {
2817 packed = true;
2818 }
2819 types.push_back(varTy);
2820
2821 byrefType->setBody(types, packed);
2822
2823 BlockByrefInfo info;
2824 info.Type = byrefType;
2825 info.FieldIndex = types.size() - 1;
2826 info.FieldOffset = varOffset;
2827 info.ByrefAlignment = std::max(varAlign, getPointerAlign());
2828
2829 auto pair = BlockByrefInfos.insert({D, info});
2830 assert(pair.second && "info was inserted recursively?");
2831 return pair.first->second;
2832}

2834/// Initialize the structural components of a __block variable, i.e.
2835/// everything but the actual object.
2836void CodeGenFunction::emitByrefStructureInit(const AutoVarEmission &emission) {
2837 // Find the address of the local.
2838 Address addr = emission.Addr;
2839
2840 // That's an alloca of the byref structure type.
2841 llvm::StructType *byrefType = cast<llvm::StructType>(
2842 cast<llvm::PointerType>(addr.getPointer()->getType())->getElementType());
2843
2844 unsigned nextHeaderIndex = 0;
2845 CharUnits nextHeaderOffset;
2846 auto storeHeaderField = [&](llvm::Value *value, CharUnits fieldSize,
2847 const Twine &name) {
2848 auto fieldAddr = Builder.CreateStructGEP(addr, nextHeaderIndex, name);
2849 Builder.CreateStore(value, fieldAddr);
2850
2851 nextHeaderIndex++;
2852 nextHeaderOffset += fieldSize;
2853 };
2854
2855 // Build the byref helpers if necessary. This is null if we don't need any.
2856 BlockByrefHelpers *helpers = buildByrefHelpers(*byrefType, emission);
2857
2858 const VarDecl &D = *emission.Variable;
2859 QualType type = D.getType();
2860
2861 bool HasByrefExtendedLayout;
2862 Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime ByrefLifetime;
2863 bool ByRefHasLifetime =
2864 getContext().getByrefLifetime(type, ByrefLifetime, HasByrefExtendedLayout);
2865
2866 llvm::Value *V;
2867
2868 // Initialize the 'isa', which is just 0 or 1.
2869 int isa = 0;
2870 if (type.isObjCGCWeak())
2871 isa = 1;
2872 V = Builder.CreateIntToPtr(Builder.getInt32(isa), Int8PtrTy, "isa");
2873 storeHeaderField(V, getPointerSize(), "byref.isa");
2874
2875 // Store the address of the variable into its own forwarding pointer.
2876 storeHeaderField(addr.getPointer(), getPointerSize(), "byref.forwarding");
2877
2878 // Blocks ABI:
2879 // c) the flags field is set to either 0 if no helper functions are
2880 // needed or BLOCK_BYREF_HAS_COPY_DISPOSE if they are,
2881 BlockFlags flags;
2882 if (helpers) flags |= BLOCK_BYREF_HAS_COPY_DISPOSE;
2883 if (ByRefHasLifetime) {
2884 if (HasByrefExtendedLayout) flags |= BLOCK_BYREF_LAYOUT_EXTENDED;
2885 else switch (ByrefLifetime) {
2886 case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
2887 flags |= BLOCK_BYREF_LAYOUT_STRONG;
2888 break;
2889 case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
2890 flags |= BLOCK_BYREF_LAYOUT_WEAK;
2891 break;
2892 case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
2893 flags |= BLOCK_BYREF_LAYOUT_UNRETAINED;
2894 break;
2895 case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
2896 if (!type->isObjCObjectPointerType() && !type->isBlockPointerType())
2897 flags |= BLOCK_BYREF_LAYOUT_NON_OBJECT;
2898 break;
2899 default:
2900 break;
2901 }
2902 if (CGM.getLangOpts().ObjCGCBitmapPrint) {
2903 printf("\n Inline flag for BYREF variable layout (%d):", flags.getBitMask());
2904 if (flags & BLOCK_BYREF_HAS_COPY_DISPOSE)
2905 printf(" BLOCK_BYREF_HAS_COPY_DISPOSE");
2906 if (flags & BLOCK_BYREF_LAYOUT_MASK) {
2907 BlockFlags ThisFlag(flags.getBitMask() & BLOCK_BYREF_LAYOUT_MASK);
2908 if (ThisFlag == BLOCK_BYREF_LAYOUT_EXTENDED)
2909 printf(" BLOCK_BYREF_LAYOUT_EXTENDED");
2910 if (ThisFlag == BLOCK_BYREF_LAYOUT_STRONG)
2911 printf(" BLOCK_BYREF_LAYOUT_STRONG");
2912 if (ThisFlag == BLOCK_BYREF_LAYOUT_WEAK)
2913 printf(" BLOCK_BYREF_LAYOUT_WEAK");
2914 if (ThisFlag == BLOCK_BYREF_LAYOUT_UNRETAINED)
2915 printf(" BLOCK_BYREF_LAYOUT_UNRETAINED");
2916 if (ThisFlag == BLOCK_BYREF_LAYOUT_NON_OBJECT)
2917 printf(" BLOCK_BYREF_LAYOUT_NON_OBJECT");
2918 }
2919 printf("\n");
2920 }
2921 }
2922 storeHeaderField(llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy, flags.getBitMask()),
2923 getIntSize(), "byref.flags");
2924
2925 CharUnits byrefSize = CGM.GetTargetTypeStoreSize(byrefType);
2926 V = llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy, byrefSize.getQuantity());
2927 storeHeaderField(V, getIntSize(), "byref.size");
2928
2929 if (helpers) {
2930 storeHeaderField(getFunctionPointer(*this, helpers->CopyHelper),
2931 getPointerSize(), "byref.copyHelper");
2932 storeHeaderField(getFunctionPointer(*this, helpers->DisposeHelper),
2933 getPointerSize(), "byref.disposeHelper");
2934 }
2935
2936 if (ByRefHasLifetime && HasByrefExtendedLayout) {
2937 auto layoutInfo = CGM.getObjCRuntime().BuildByrefLayout(CGM, type);
2938 storeHeaderField(layoutInfo, getPointerSize(), "byref.layout");
2939 }
2940}

2963/// Adjust the declaration of something from the blocks API.
2964static void configureBlocksRuntimeObject(CodeGenModule &CGM,
2965 llvm::Constant *C) {
2966 auto *GV = cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(C->stripPointerCasts());
2967
2968 if (CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF()) {
2969 IdentifierInfo &II = CGM.getContext().Idents.get(C->getName());
2970 TranslationUnitDecl *TUDecl = CGM.getContext().getTranslationUnitDecl();
2971 DeclContext *DC = TranslationUnitDecl::castToDeclContext(TUDecl);
2972
2973 assert((isa<llvm::Function>(C->stripPointerCasts()) ||
2974 isa<llvm::GlobalVariable>(C->stripPointerCasts())) &&
2975 "expected Function or GlobalVariable");
2976
2977 const NamedDecl *ND = nullptr;
2978 for (const auto &Result : DC->lookup(&II))
2979 if ((ND = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Result)) ||
2980 (ND = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(Result)))
2981 break;
2982
2983 // TODO: support static blocks runtime
2984 if (GV->isDeclaration() && (!ND || !ND->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>())) {
2985 GV->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLImportStorageClass);
2986 GV->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage);
2987 } else {
2988 GV->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLExportStorageClass);
2989 GV->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage);
2990 }
2991 }
2992
2993 if (CGM.getLangOpts().BlocksRuntimeOptional && GV->isDeclaration() &&
2994 GV->hasExternalLinkage())
2995 GV->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalWeakLinkage);
2996
2997 CGM.setDSOLocal(GV);
2998}
